v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

53// Aliases to avoid having to repeat the class.
54// With C++20 we can use "using" to introduce scoped enums.
55constexpr InlineCacheState NO_FEEDBACK = InlineCacheState::NO_FEEDBACK;
56constexpr InlineCacheState UNINITIALIZED = InlineCacheState::UNINITIALIZED;
57constexpr InlineCacheState MONOMORPHIC = InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC;
58constexpr InlineCacheState RECOMPUTE_HANDLER =
59 InlineCacheState::RECOMPUTE_HANDLER;
60constexpr InlineCacheState POLYMORPHIC = InlineCacheState::POLYMORPHIC;
61constexpr InlineCacheState MEGAMORPHIC = InlineCacheState::MEGAMORPHIC;
62constexpr InlineCacheState MEGADOM = InlineCacheState::MEGADOM;
63constexpr InlineCacheState GENERIC = InlineCacheState::GENERIC;
64
65char IC::TransitionMarkFromState(IC::State state) {
66 switch (state) {
67 case NO_FEEDBACK:
68 return 'X';
69 case UNINITIALIZED:
70 return '0';
71 case MONOMORPHIC:
72 return '1';
73 case RECOMPUTE_HANDLER:
74 return '^';
75 case POLYMORPHIC:
76 return 'P';
77 case MEGAMORPHIC:
78 return 'N';
79 case MEGADOM:
80 return 'D';
81 case GENERIC:
82 return 'G';
83 }
84 UNREACHABLE();
85}

89const char* GetModifier(KeyedAccessLoadMode mode) {
90 switch (mode) {
91 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB:
92 return ".OOB";
93 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles:
94 return ".HOLES";
95 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles:
96 return ".OOB+HOLES";
97 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds:
98 return "";
99 }
100}
101
102const char* GetModifier(KeyedAccessStoreMode mode) {
103 switch (mode) {
104 case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW:
105 return ".COW";
106 case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW:
107 return ".STORE+COW";
108 case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kIgnoreTypedArrayOOB:
109 return ".IGNORE_OOB";
110 case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds:
111 return "";
112 }
113 UNREACHABLE();
114}

118void IC::TraceIC(const char* type, DirectHandle<Object> name) {
119 if (V8_LIKELY(!TracingFlags::is_ic_stats_enabled())) return;
120 State new_state =
121 (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) ? NO_FEEDBACK : nexus()->ic_state();
122 TraceIC(type, name, state(), new_state);
123}
124
125void IC::TraceIC(const char* type, DirectHandle<Object> name, State old_state,
126 State new_state) {
127 if (V8_LIKELY(!TracingFlags::is_ic_stats_enabled())) return;
128
129 DirectHandle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map(); // Might be empty.
130
131 const char* modifier = "";
132 if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
133 modifier = "";
134 } else if (IsKeyedLoadIC()) {
135 KeyedAccessLoadMode mode = nexus()->GetKeyedAccessLoadMode();
136 modifier = GetModifier(mode);
137 } else if (IsKeyedStoreIC() || IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC() ||
138 IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
139 KeyedAccessStoreMode mode = nexus()->GetKeyedAccessStoreMode();
140 modifier = GetModifier(mode);
141 }
142
143 bool keyed_prefix = is_keyed() && !IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC();
144
145 if (!(TracingFlags::ic_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
146 v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
147 LOG(isolate(), ICEvent(type, keyed_prefix, map, name,
148 TransitionMarkFromState(old_state),
149 TransitionMarkFromState(new_state), modifier,
150 slow_stub_reason_));
151 return;
152 }
153
154 JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate());
155 JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
156
157 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
158 Tagged<JSFunction> function = frame->function();
159
160 ICStats::instance()->Begin();
161 ICInfo& ic_info = ICStats::instance()->Current();
162 ic_info.type = keyed_prefix ? "Keyed" : "";
163 ic_info.type += type;
164
165 int code_offset = 0;
166 Tagged<AbstractCode> code;
167 std::tie(code, code_offset) = frame->GetActiveCodeAndOffset();
168 JavaScriptFrame::CollectFunctionAndOffsetForICStats(isolate(), function, code,
169 code_offset);
170
171 // Reserve enough space for IC transition state, the longest length is 17.
172 ic_info.state.reserve(17);
173 ic_info.state = "(";
174 ic_info.state += TransitionMarkFromState(old_state);
175 ic_info.state += "->";
176 ic_info.state += TransitionMarkFromState(new_state);
177 ic_info.state += modifier;
178 ic_info.state += ")";
179 if (!map.is_null()) {
180 ic_info.map = reinterpret_cast<void*>(map->ptr());
181 ic_info.is_dictionary_map = map->is_dictionary_map();
182 ic_info.number_of_own_descriptors = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
183 ic_info.instance_type = std::to_string(map->instance_type());
184 } else {
185 ic_info.map = nullptr;
186 }
187 // TODO(lpy) Add name as key field in ICStats.
188 ICStats::instance()->End();
189}

191IC::IC(Isolate* isolate, Handle<FeedbackVector> vector, FeedbackSlot slot,
192 FeedbackSlotKind kind)
193 : isolate_(isolate),
194 vector_set_(false),
195 kind_(kind),
196 target_maps_set_(false),
197 slow_stub_reason_(nullptr),
198 nexus_(isolate, vector, slot) {
199 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!vector.is_null(), kind_ == nexus_.kind());
200 state_ = (vector.is_null()) ? NO_FEEDBACK : nexus_.ic_state();
201 old_state_ = state_;
202}

204static void LookupForRead(LookupIterator* it, bool is_has_property) {
205 for (;; it->Next()) {
206 switch (it->state()) {
207 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
208 UNREACHABLE();
209 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
210 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
211 return;
212 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
213 // If there is a getter, return; otherwise loop to perform the lookup.
214 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
215 if (!IsUndefined(holder->GetNamedInterceptor()->getter(),
216 it->isolate())) {
217 return;
218 }
219 if (is_has_property &&
220 !IsUndefined(holder->GetNamedInterceptor()->query(),
221 it->isolate())) {
222 return;
223 }
224 continue;
225 }
226 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
227 // ICs know how to perform access checks on global proxies.
228 if (it->GetHolder<JSObject>().is_identical_to(
229 it->isolate()->global_proxy()) &&
230 !it->isolate()->global_object()->IsDetached()) {
231 continue;
232 }
233 return;
234 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
235 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
236 case LookupIterator::DATA:
237 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
238 return;
239 }
240 UNREACHABLE();
241 }
242}

244bool IC::ShouldRecomputeHandler(DirectHandle<String> name) {
245 if (!RecomputeHandlerForName(name)) return false;
246
247 // This is a contextual access, always just update the handler and stay
248 // monomorphic.
249 if (IsGlobalIC()) return true;
250
251 MaybeObjectHandle maybe_handler =
252 nexus()->FindHandlerForMap(lookup_start_object_map());
253
254 // The current map wasn't handled yet. There's no reason to stay monomorphic,
255 // *unless* we're moving from a deprecated map to its replacement, or
256 // to a more general elements kind.
257 // TODO(verwaest): Check if the current map is actually what the old map
258 // would transition to.
259 if (maybe_handler.is_null()) {
260 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*lookup_start_object_map())) return false;
261 Tagged<Map> first_map = FirstTargetMap();
262 if (first_map.is_null()) return false;
263 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(first_map, isolate());
264 if (old_map->is_deprecated()) return true;
265 return IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
266 old_map->elements_kind(), lookup_start_object_map()->elements_kind());
267 }
268
269 return true;
270}
271
272bool IC::RecomputeHandlerForName(DirectHandle<Object> name) {
273 if (is_keyed()) {
274 // Determine whether the failure is due to a name failure.
275 if (!IsName(*name)) return false;
276 Tagged<Name> stub_name = nexus()->GetName();
277 if (*name != stub_name) return false;
278 }
279
280 return true;
281}
282
283void IC::UpdateState(DirectHandle<Object> lookup_start_object,
284 DirectHandle<Object> name) {
285 if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) return;
286 update_lookup_start_object_map(lookup_start_object);
287 if (!IsString(*name)) return;
288 if (state() != MONOMORPHIC && state() != POLYMORPHIC) return;
289 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*lookup_start_object, isolate())) return;
290
291 // Remove the target from the code cache if it became invalid
292 // because of changes in the prototype chain to avoid hitting it
293 // again.
294 if (ShouldRecomputeHandler(Cast<String>(name))) {
295 MarkRecomputeHandler(name);
296 }
297}

300 Handle<Object> key) {
301 HandleScope scope(isolate());
302 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(), NewTypeError(index, key, object));

305MaybeHandle<Object> IC::ReferenceError(Handle<Name> name) {
306 HandleScope scope(isolate());

308 NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kNotDefined, name));
309}

311void IC::OnFeedbackChanged(const char* reason) {
312 vector_set_ = true;
313 Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector = nexus()->vector();
314 FeedbackSlot slot = nexus()->slot();
315 OnFeedbackChanged(isolate(), vector, slot, reason);
316}
317
318// static
319void IC::OnFeedbackChanged(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector,
320 FeedbackSlot slot, const char* reason) {
321#ifdef V8_TRACE_FEEDBACK_UPDATES
322 if (v8_flags.trace_feedback_updates) {
323 FeedbackVector::TraceFeedbackChange(isolate, vector, slot, reason);
324 }
325#endif
326
327 isolate->tiering_manager()->NotifyICChanged(vector);
328}

332bool MigrateDeprecated(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
333 if (!IsJSObject(*object)) return false;
334 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(object);
335 if (!receiver->map()->is_deprecated()) return false;
336 JSObject::MigrateInstance(isolate, receiver);
337 return true;
338}

342bool IC::ConfigureVectorState(IC::State new_state, DirectHandle<Object> key) {
343 DCHECK_EQ(MEGAMORPHIC, new_state);
344 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!is_keyed(), IsName(*key));
345 bool changed = nexus()->ConfigureMegamorphic(
346 IsName(*key) ? IcCheckType::kProperty : IcCheckType::kElement);
347 if (changed) {
348 OnFeedbackChanged("Megamorphic");
349 }
350 return changed;
351}

353void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Map> map,
354 Handle<Object> handler) {
355 ConfigureVectorState(name, map, MaybeObjectHandle(handler));
356}
357
358void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Map> map,
359 const MaybeObjectHandle& handler) {
360 if (IsGlobalIC()) {
361 nexus()->ConfigureHandlerMode(handler);
362 } else {
363 // Non-keyed ICs don't track the name explicitly.
364 if (!is_keyed()) name = Handle<Name>::null();
365 nexus()->ConfigureMonomorphic(name, map, handler);
366 }
367
368 OnFeedbackChanged(IsLoadGlobalIC() ? "LoadGlobal" : "Monomorphic");
369}
370
371void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name, MapHandlesSpan maps,
372 MaybeObjectHandles* handlers) {
373 DCHECK(!IsGlobalIC());
374 MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers;
375 maps_and_handlers.reserve(maps.size());
376 DCHECK_EQ(maps.size(), handlers->size());
377 for (size_t i = 0; i < maps.size(); i++) {
378 maps_and_handlers.push_back(MapAndHandler(maps[i], handlers->at(i)));
379 }
380 ConfigureVectorState(name, maps_and_handlers);
381}
382
383void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name,
384 MapsAndHandlers const& maps_and_handlers) {
385 DCHECK(!IsGlobalIC());
386 // Non-keyed ICs don't track the name explicitly.
387 if (!is_keyed()) name = Handle<Name>::null();
388 nexus()->ConfigurePolymorphic(name, maps_and_handlers);
389
390 OnFeedbackChanged("Polymorphic");
391}

393MaybeHandle<Object> LoadIC::Load(Handle<JSAny> object, Handle<Name> name,
394 bool update_feedback,
395 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver) {
396 bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic && update_feedback;
397
398 if (receiver.is_null()) {
399 receiver = object;
400 }
401
402 // If the object is undefined or null it's illegal to try to get any
403 // of its properties; throw a TypeError in that case.
404 if (IsAnyHas() ? !IsJSReceiver(*object)
405 : IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate())) {
406 if (use_ic) {
407 // Ensure the IC state progresses.
408 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_NonReceiver);
409 update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
410 SetCache(name, LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
411 TraceIC("LoadIC", name);
412 }
413
414 if (*name == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).iterator_symbol()) {
415 isolate()->Throw(*ErrorUtils::NewIteratorError(isolate(), object));
416 return MaybeHandle<Object>();
417 }
418
419 if (IsAnyHas()) {
420 return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidInOperatorUse, object, name);
421 } else {
422 DCHECK(IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate()));
423 ErrorUtils::ThrowLoadFromNullOrUndefined(isolate(), object, name);
424 return MaybeHandle<Object>();
425 }
426 }
427
428 // If we encounter an object with a deprecated map, we want to update the
429 // feedback vector with the migrated map.
430 // Mark ourselves as RECOMPUTE_HANDLER so that we don't turn megamorphic due
431 // to seeing the same map and handler.
432 if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
433 UpdateState(object, name);
434 }
435
436 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtReceiver, isolate());
437 update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
438
439 PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
440 LookupIterator it = LookupIterator(isolate(), receiver, key, object);
441
442 // Named lookup in the object.
443 LookupForRead(&it, IsAnyHas());
444
445 if (it.IsFound() || !ShouldThrowReferenceError()) {
446 // Update inline cache and stub cache.
447 if (use_ic) {
448 UpdateCaches(&it);
449 } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
450 // Tracing IC stats
451 IsLoadGlobalIC() ? TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name)
452 : TraceIC("LoadIC", name);
453 }
454
455 if (IsAnyHas()) {
456 // Named lookup in the object.
457 Maybe<bool> maybe = JSReceiver::HasProperty(&it);
458 if (maybe.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
459 return isolate()->factory()->ToBoolean(maybe.FromJust());
460 }
461
462 // Get the property.
463 Handle<Object> result;
464
465 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
466 Object::GetProperty(&it, IsLoadGlobalIC()));
467 if (it.IsFound()) {
468 return result;
469 } else if (!ShouldThrowReferenceError()) {
470 return result;
471 }
472 }
473 return ReferenceError(name);
474}
475
476MaybeHandle<Object> LoadGlobalIC::Load(Handle<Name> name,
477 bool update_feedback) {
478 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global = isolate()->global_object();
479
480 if (IsString(*name)) {
481 // Look up in script context table.
482 DirectHandle<String> str_name = Cast<String>(name);
483 DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
484 global->native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
485
486 VariableLookupResult lookup_result;
487 if (script_contexts->Lookup(str_name, &lookup_result)) {
488 DirectHandle<Context> script_context(
489 script_contexts->get(lookup_result.context_index), isolate());
490 Handle<Object> result(script_context->get(lookup_result.slot_index),
491 isolate());
492
493 if (IsTheHole(*result, isolate())) {
494 // Do not install stubs and stay pre-monomorphic for
495 // uninitialized accesses.
496 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
497 isolate(),
498 NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kAccessedUninitializedVariable,
499 name));
500 }
501
502 bool use_ic =
503 (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic && update_feedback;
504 if (use_ic) {
505 // 'const' Variables are mutable if REPL mode is enabled. This disables
506 // compiler inlining for all 'const' variables declared in REPL mode.
507 if (nexus()->ConfigureLexicalVarMode(
508 lookup_result.context_index, lookup_result.slot_index,
509 (IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode) &&
510 !lookup_result.is_repl_mode))) {
511 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadGlobalIC_LoadScriptContextField);
512 } else {
513 // Given combination of indices can't be encoded, so use slow stub.
514 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadGlobalIC_SlowStub);
515 SetCache(name, LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
516 }
517 TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name);
518 } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
519 TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name);
520 }
521 if (v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number) {
522 return handle(
523 *Context::LoadScriptContextElement(
524 script_context, lookup_result.slot_index, result, isolate()),
525 isolate());
526 }
527 return result;
528 }
529 }
530 return LoadIC::Load(global, name, update_feedback);
531}

535bool AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(MapHandles* receiver_maps,
536 Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
537 DCHECK(!new_receiver_map.is_null());
538 for (DirectHandle<Map> map : *receiver_maps) {
539 if (!map.is_null() && map.is_identical_to(new_receiver_map)) {
540 return false;
541 }
542 }
543 receiver_maps->push_back(new_receiver_map);
544 return true;
545}
546
547bool AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(MapsAndHandlers* receiver_maps_and_handlers,
548 Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
549 DCHECK(!new_receiver_map.is_null());
550 if (new_receiver_map->is_deprecated()) return false;
551 for (MapAndHandler map_and_handler : *receiver_maps_and_handlers) {
552 DirectHandle<Map> map = map_and_handler.first;
553 if (!map.is_null() && map.is_identical_to(new_receiver_map)) {
554 return false;
555 }
556 }
557 receiver_maps_and_handlers->push_back(
558 MapAndHandler(new_receiver_map, MaybeObjectHandle()));
559 return true;
560}

562Handle<NativeContext> GetAccessorContext(
563 const CallOptimization& call_optimization, Tagged<Map> holder_map,
564 Isolate* isolate) {
565 std::optional<Tagged<NativeContext>> maybe_context =
566 call_optimization.GetAccessorContext(holder_map);
567
568 // Holders which are remote objects are not expected in the IC system.
569 CHECK(maybe_context.has_value());
570 return handle(maybe_context.value(), isolate);
571}

575bool IC::UpdateMegaDOMIC(const MaybeObjectHandle& handler,
576 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
577 if (!v8_flags.mega_dom_ic) return false;
578
579 // TODO(gsathya): Enable fuzzing once this feature is more stable.
580 if (v8_flags.fuzzing) return false;
581
582 // TODO(gsathya): Support KeyedLoadIC, StoreIC and KeyedStoreIC.
583 if (!IsLoadIC()) return false;
584
585 // Check if DOM protector cell is valid.
586 if (!Protectors::IsMegaDOMIntact(isolate())) return false;
587
588 // Check if current lookup object is an API object
589 Handle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
590 if (!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(map->instance_type())) return false;
591
592 Handle<Object> accessor_obj;
593 // TODO(gsathya): Check if there are overloads possible for this accessor and
594 // transition only if it isn't possible.
595 if (!accessor().ToHandle(&accessor_obj)) return false;
596
597 // TODO(gsathya): This is also created in IC::ComputeHandler, find a way to
598 // reuse it here.
599 CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), accessor_obj);
600
601 // Check if accessor is an API function
602 if (!call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) return false;
603
604 // Check if accessor requires access checks
605 if (call_optimization.accept_any_receiver()) return false;
606
607 // Check if accessor requires signature checks
608 if (!call_optimization.requires_signature_check()) return false;
609
610 // Check if the receiver is the holder
611 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
612 call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(isolate(), map, &holder_lookup);
613 if (holder_lookup != CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver) return false;
614
615 Handle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
616 GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, *map, isolate());
617
618 Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> fti;
619 if (IsJSFunction(*accessor_obj)) {
620 fti = handle(Cast<JSFunction>(*accessor_obj)->shared()->api_func_data(),
621 isolate());
622 } else {
623 fti = Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(accessor_obj);
624 }
625
626 Handle<MegaDomHandler> new_handler = isolate()->factory()->NewMegaDomHandler(
627 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(fti), MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(accessor_context));
628 nexus()->ConfigureMegaDOM(MaybeObjectHandle(new_handler));
629 return true;
630}
631
632bool IC::UpdatePolymorphicIC(DirectHandle<Name> name,
633 const MaybeObjectHandle& handler) {
634 DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
635 if (is_keyed() && state() != RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
636 if (nexus()->GetName() != *name) return false;
637 }
638 Handle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
639
640 MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers;
641 maps_and_handlers.reserve(v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count);
642 int deprecated_maps = 0;
643 int handler_to_overwrite = -1;
644
645 {
646 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
647 int i = 0;
648 for (FeedbackIterator it(nexus()); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
649 if (it.handler().IsCleared()) continue;
650 MaybeObjectHandle existing_handler = handle(it.handler(), isolate());
651 Handle<Map> existing_map = handle(it.map(), isolate());
652
653 maps_and_handlers.push_back(
654 MapAndHandler(existing_map, existing_handler));
655
656 if (existing_map->is_deprecated()) {
657 // Filter out deprecated maps to ensure their instances get migrated.
658 deprecated_maps++;
659 } else if (map.is_identical_to(existing_map)) {
660 // If both map and handler stayed the same (and the name is also the
661 // same as checked above, for keyed accesses), we're not progressing
662 // in the lattice and need to go MEGAMORPHIC instead. There's one
663 // exception to this rule, which is when we're in RECOMPUTE_HANDLER
664 // state, there we allow to migrate to a new handler.
665 if (handler.is_identical_to(existing_handler) &&
666 state() != RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
667 return false;
668 }
669
670 // If the receiver type is already in the polymorphic IC, this indicates
671 // there was a prototoype chain failure. In that case, just overwrite
672 // the handler.
673 handler_to_overwrite = i;
674 } else if (handler_to_overwrite == -1 &&
675 IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*existing_map, *map)) {
676 handler_to_overwrite = i;
677 }
678
679 i++;
680 }
681 DCHECK_LE(i, maps_and_handlers.size());
682 }
683
684 int number_of_maps = static_cast<int>(maps_and_handlers.size());
685 int number_of_valid_maps =
686 number_of_maps - deprecated_maps - (handler_to_overwrite != -1);
687
688 if (number_of_valid_maps >= v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
689 return false;
690 }
691 if (deprecated_maps >= v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
692 return false;
693 }
694 if (number_of_maps == 0 && state() != MONOMORPHIC && state() != POLYMORPHIC) {
695 return false;
696 }
697
698 number_of_valid_maps++;
699 if (number_of_valid_maps == 1) {
700 ConfigureVectorState(name, lookup_start_object_map(), handler);
701 } else {
702 if (is_keyed() && nexus()->GetName() != *name) return false;
703 if (handler_to_overwrite >= 0) {
704 maps_and_handlers[handler_to_overwrite].second = handler;
705 if (!map.is_identical_to(
706 maps_and_handlers.at(handler_to_overwrite).first)) {
707 maps_and_handlers[handler_to_overwrite].first = map;
708 }
709 } else {
710 maps_and_handlers.push_back(MapAndHandler(map, handler));
711 }
712
713 ConfigureVectorState(name, maps_and_handlers);
714 }
715
716 return true;
717}
718
719void IC::UpdateMonomorphicIC(const MaybeObjectHandle& handler,
720 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
721 DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
722 ConfigureVectorState(name, lookup_start_object_map(), handler);
723}
724
725void IC::CopyICToMegamorphicCache(DirectHandle<Name> name) {
726 MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers;
727 nexus()->ExtractMapsAndHandlers(&maps_and_handlers);
728 for (const MapAndHandler& map_and_handler : maps_and_handlers) {
729 UpdateMegamorphicCache(map_and_handler.first, name, map_and_handler.second);
730 }
731}
732
733bool IC::IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(Tagged<Map> source_map,
734 Tagged<Map> target_map) {
735 if (source_map.is_null()) return true;
736 if (target_map.is_null()) return false;
737 if (source_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) return false;
738 ElementsKind target_elements_kind = target_map->elements_kind();
739 bool more_general_transition = IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
740 source_map->elements_kind(), target_elements_kind);
741 Tagged<Map> transitioned_map;
742 if (more_general_transition) {
743 Handle<Map> single_map[1] = {handle(target_map, isolate_)};
744 transitioned_map = source_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
745 isolate(), single_map, ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
746 }
747 return transitioned_map == target_map;
748}
749
750void IC::SetCache(DirectHandle<Name> name, Handle<Object> handler) {
751 SetCache(name, MaybeObjectHandle(handler));
752}
753
754void IC::SetCache(DirectHandle<Name> name, const MaybeObjectHandle& handler) {
755 DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
756 // Currently only load and store ICs support non-code handlers.
757 DCHECK(IsAnyLoad() || IsAnyStore() || IsAnyHas());
758 switch (state()) {
759 case NO_FEEDBACK:
760 UNREACHABLE();
761 case UNINITIALIZED:
762 UpdateMonomorphicIC(handler, name);
763 break;
764 case RECOMPUTE_HANDLER:
765 case MONOMORPHIC:
766 if (IsGlobalIC()) {
767 UpdateMonomorphicIC(handler, name);
768 break;
769 }
770 [[fallthrough]];
771 case POLYMORPHIC:
772 if (UpdatePolymorphicIC(name, handler)) break;
773 if (UpdateMegaDOMIC(handler, name)) break;
774 if (!is_keyed() || state() == RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
775 CopyICToMegamorphicCache(name);
776 }
777 [[fallthrough]];
778 case MEGADOM:
779 ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, name);
780 [[fallthrough]];
781 case MEGAMORPHIC:
782 UpdateMegamorphicCache(lookup_start_object_map(), name, handler);
783 // Indicate that we've handled this case.
784 vector_set_ = true;
785 break;
786 case GENERIC:
787 UNREACHABLE();
788 }
789}
790
791void LoadIC::UpdateCaches(LookupIterator* lookup) {
792 MaybeObjectHandle handler;
793 if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
794 handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
795 } else if (!lookup->IsFound()) {
796 if (lookup->IsPrivateName()) {
797 handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
798 } else {
799 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNonexistentDH);
800 Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNonExistent(isolate());
801 handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFullChain(
802 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(),
803 MaybeObjectHandle(isolate()->factory()->null_value()), smi_handler));
804 }
805 } else if (IsLoadGlobalIC() && lookup->state() == LookupIterator::JSPROXY) {
806 // If there is proxy just install the slow stub since we need to call the
807 // HasProperty trap for global loads. The ProxyGetProperty builtin doesn't
808 // handle this case.
809 handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
810 } else {
811 if (IsLoadGlobalIC()) {
812 if (lookup->TryLookupCachedProperty()) {
813 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, lookup->state());
814 }
815 if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
816 lookup->GetReceiver().is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<Object>())) {
817 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup->GetReceiver()));
818 // Now update the cell in the feedback vector.
819 nexus()->ConfigurePropertyCellMode(lookup->GetPropertyCell());
820 TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", lookup->name());
821 return;
822 }
823 }
824 handler = ComputeHandler(lookup);
825 auto holder = lookup->GetHolder<Object>();
826 CHECK(*holder == *(lookup->lookup_start_object()) ||
827 LoadHandler::CanHandleHolderNotLookupStart(*handler.object()) ||
828 IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*holder));
829 }
830 // Can't use {lookup->name()} because the LookupIterator might be in
831 // "elements" mode for keys that are strings representing integers above
832 // JSArray::kMaxIndex.
833 SetCache(lookup->GetName(), handler);
834 TraceIC("LoadIC", lookup->GetName());
835}
836
837StubCache* IC::stub_cache() {
838 // HasICs and each of the store own ICs require its own stub cache.
839 // Until we create them, don't allow accessing the load/store stub caches.
840 DCHECK(!IsAnyHas());
841 if (IsAnyLoad()) {
842 return isolate()->load_stub_cache();
843 } else if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
844 return isolate()->define_own_stub_cache();
845 } else {
846 DCHECK(IsAnyStore());
847 return isolate()->store_stub_cache();
848 }
849}
850
851void IC::UpdateMegamorphicCache(DirectHandle<Map> map, DirectHandle<Name> name,
852 const MaybeObjectHandle& handler) {
853 if (!IsAnyHas()) {
854 stub_cache()->Set(*name, *map, *handler);
855 }
856}
857
858MaybeObjectHandle LoadIC::ComputeHandler(LookupIterator* lookup) {
859 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = lookup->GetReceiver();
860 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
861
862 DirectHandle<Object> lookup_start_object = lookup->lookup_start_object();
863 // `in` cannot be called on strings, and will always return true for string
864 // wrapper length and function prototypes. The latter two cases are given
865 // LoadHandler::LoadNativeDataProperty below.
866 if (!IsAnyHas() && !lookup->IsElement()) {
867 if (IsString(*lookup_start_object) &&
868 *lookup->name() == roots.length_string()) {
869 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_StringLength);
870 return MaybeObjectHandle(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_StringLength));
871 }
872
873 if (IsStringWrapper(*lookup_start_object) &&
874 *lookup->name() == roots.length_string()) {
875 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_StringWrapperLength);
876 return MaybeObjectHandle(
877 BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_StringWrapperLength));
878 }
879
880 // Use specialized code for getting prototype of functions.
881 if (IsJSFunction(*lookup_start_object) &&
882 *lookup->name() == roots.prototype_string() &&
883 !Cast<JSFunction>(*lookup_start_object)
884 ->PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup()) {
885 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_FunctionPrototypeStub);
886 return MaybeObjectHandle(
887 BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_FunctionPrototype));
888 }
889 }
890
891 Handle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
892 bool holder_is_lookup_start_object =
893 lookup_start_object.is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<JSReceiver>());
894
895 switch (lookup->state()) {
896 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
897 Handle<JSObject> holder =
898 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
899 Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadInterceptor(isolate());
900
901 if (holder->GetNamedInterceptor()->non_masking()) {
902 MaybeObjectHandle holder_ref(isolate()->factory()->null_value());
903 if (!holder_is_lookup_start_object || IsLoadGlobalIC()) {
904 holder_ref = MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(holder);
905 }
906 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNonMaskingInterceptorDH);
907 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFullChain(
908 isolate(), map, holder_ref, smi_handler));
909 }
910
911 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
912 DCHECK(map->has_named_interceptor());
913 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadInterceptorDH);
914 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
915 }
916
917 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadInterceptorFromPrototypeDH);
918 return MaybeObjectHandle(
919 LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
920 }
921
922 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
923 Handle<JSObject> holder =
924 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
925 // Use simple field loads for some well-known callback properties.
926 // The method will only return true for absolute truths based on the
927 // lookup start object maps.
928 FieldIndex field_index;
929 if (Accessors::IsJSObjectFieldAccessor(isolate(), map, lookup->name(),
930 &field_index)) {
931 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldDH);
932 return MaybeObjectHandle(
933 LoadHandler::LoadField(isolate(), field_index));
934 }
935 if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*holder)) {
936 DirectHandle<ObjectHashTable> exports(
937 Cast<JSModuleNamespace>(holder)->module()->exports(), isolate());
938 InternalIndex entry =
939 exports->FindEntry(isolate(), roots, lookup->name(),
940 Smi::ToInt(Object::GetHash(*lookup->name())));
941 // We found the accessor, so the entry must exist.
942 DCHECK(entry.is_found());
943 int value_index = ObjectHashTable::EntryToValueIndex(entry);
944 Handle<Smi> smi_handler =
945 LoadHandler::LoadModuleExport(isolate(), value_index);
946 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
947 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
948 }
949 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
950 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
951 }
952
953 DirectHandle<Object> accessors = lookup->GetAccessors();
954 if (IsAccessorPair(*accessors)) {
955 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair =
956 Cast<AccessorPair>(accessors);
957 if (lookup->TryLookupCachedProperty(accessor_pair)) {
958 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, lookup->state());
959 return MaybeObjectHandle(ComputeHandler(lookup));
960 }
961
962 Handle<Object> getter(accessor_pair->getter(), isolate());
963 if (!IsCallableJSFunction(*getter) &&
964 !IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
965 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
966 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
967 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
968 }
969 set_accessor(getter);
970
971 if ((IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter) &&
972 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*getter)->BreakAtEntry(isolate())) ||
973 (IsJSFunction(*getter) &&
974 Cast<JSFunction>(*getter)->shared()->BreakAtEntry(isolate()))) {
975 // Do not install an IC if the api function has a breakpoint.
976 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
977 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
978 }
979
980 Handle<Smi> smi_handler;
981
982 CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), getter);
983 if (call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) {
984 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
985 DirectHandle<JSObject> api_holder =
986 call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(isolate(), map,
987 &holder_lookup);
988
989 if (!call_optimization.IsCompatibleReceiverMap(api_holder, holder,
990 holder_lookup) ||
991 !holder->HasFastProperties()) {
992 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
993 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
994 }
995
996 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadApiGetter(
997 isolate(), holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
998
999 Handle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
1000 GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, holder->map(), isolate());
1001
1002 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadApiGetterFromPrototypeDH);
1003 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1004 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1005 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(call_optimization.api_call_info()),
1006 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(accessor_context)));
1007 }
1008
1009 if (holder->HasFastProperties()) {
1010 DCHECK(IsCallableJSFunction(*getter));
1011 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
1012 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadAccessorDH);
1013 return MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
1014 indirect_handle(accessor_pair, isolate()));
1015 }
1016 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadAccessorFromPrototypeDH);
1017 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1018 isolate(), map, holder,
1019 *LoadHandler::LoadAccessorFromPrototype(isolate()),
1020 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(getter)));
1021 }
1022
1023 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder)) {
1024 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadGlobalFromPrototypeDH);
1025 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadGlobal(isolate());
1026 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1027 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1028 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
1029 indirect_handle(lookup->GetPropertyCell(), isolate()))));
1030 } else {
1031 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNormal(isolate());
1032 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalDH);
1033 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1034 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1035 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalFromPrototypeDH);
1036 }
1037
1038 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1039 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1040 }
1041
1042 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(accessors);
1043
1044 if (info->replace_on_access()) {
1045 set_slow_stub_reason(
1046 "getter needs to be reconfigured to data property");
1047 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1048 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1049 }
1050
1051 if (!info->has_getter(isolate()) || !holder->HasFastProperties() ||
1052 (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver))) {
1053 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1054 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1055 }
1056
1057 Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNativeDataProperty(
1058 isolate(), lookup->GetAccessorIndex());
1059 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNativeDataPropertyDH);
1060 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1061 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
1062 LoadIC_LoadNativeDataPropertyFromPrototypeDH);
1063 return MaybeObjectHandle(
1064 LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1065 }
1066
1067 case LookupIterator::DATA: {
1068 Handle<JSReceiver> holder =
1069 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSReceiver>(), isolate());
1070 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, lookup->property_details().kind());
1071 Handle<Smi> smi_handler;
1072 if (lookup->is_dictionary_holder()) {
1073 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder, isolate())) {
1074 // TODO(verwaest): Also supporting the global object as receiver is a
1075 // workaround for code that leaks the global object.
1076 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadGlobalDH);
1077 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadGlobal(isolate());
1078 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1079 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1080 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
1081 indirect_handle(lookup->GetPropertyCell(), isolate()))));
1082 }
1083 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNormal(isolate());
1084 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalDH);
1085 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1086 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1087 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalFromPrototypeDH);
1088 } else if (lookup->IsElement(*holder)) {
1089 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1090 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1091 } else {
1092 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField,
1093 lookup->property_details().location());
1094 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*holder, isolate()));
1095 FieldIndex field = lookup->GetFieldIndex();
1096 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadField(isolate(), field);
1097 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldDH);
1098 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1099 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1100 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldFromPrototypeDH);
1101 }
1102 if (lookup->constness() == PropertyConstness::kConst &&
1103 !holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
1104 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
1105 !lookup->is_dictionary_holder());
1106
1107 DirectHandle<Object> value = lookup->GetDataValue();
1108
1109 if (IsThinString(*value)) {
1110 value = direct_handle(Cast<ThinString>(*value)->actual(), isolate());
1111 }
1112
1113 // Non internalized strings could turn into thin/cons strings
1114 // when internalized. Weak references to thin/cons strings are
1115 // not supported in the GC. If concurrent marking is running
1116 // and the thin/cons string is marked but the actual string is
1117 // not, then the weak reference could be missed.
1118 if (!IsString(*value) ||
1119 (IsString(*value) && IsInternalizedString(*value))) {
1120 MaybeObjectHandle weak_value =
1121 IsSmi(*value) ? MaybeObjectHandle(*value, isolate())
1122 : MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(*value, isolate());
1123
1124 smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadConstantFromPrototype(isolate());
1125 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadConstantFromPrototypeDH);
1126 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1127 isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler, weak_value));
1128 }
1129 }
1130 return MaybeObjectHandle(
1131 LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1132 }
1133 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1134 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadIntegerIndexedExoticDH);
1135 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadNonExistent(isolate()));
1136
1137 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1138 // Private names on JSProxy is currently not supported.
1139 if (lookup->name()->IsPrivate()) {
1140 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1141 }
1142 Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadProxy(isolate());
1143 if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1144
1145 Handle<JSProxy> holder_proxy =
1146 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), isolate());
1147 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1148 isolate(), map, holder_proxy, *smi_handler));
1149 }
1150
1151 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1152 return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1153 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1154 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1155 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1156 UNREACHABLE();
1157 }
1158
1159 return MaybeObjectHandle(Handle<InstructionStream>::null());
1160}
1161
1162KeyedAccessLoadMode KeyedLoadIC::GetKeyedAccessLoadModeFor(
1163 DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map) const {
1164 const MaybeObjectHandle& handler = nexus()->FindHandlerForMap(receiver_map);
1165 if (handler.is_null()) return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1166 return LoadHandler::GetKeyedAccessLoadMode(*handler);
1167}
1168
1169// Returns whether the load mode transition is allowed.
1170bool AllowedHandlerChange(KeyedAccessLoadMode old_mode,
1171 KeyedAccessLoadMode new_mode) {
1172 // Only allow transitions to allow OOB or allow converting a hole to
1173 // undefined.
1174 using T = std::underlying_type_t<KeyedAccessLoadMode>;
1175 return ((static_cast<T>(old_mode) ^
1176 static_cast<T>(GeneralizeKeyedAccessLoadMode(old_mode, new_mode))) &
1177 0b11) != 0;
1178}
1179
1180void KeyedLoadIC::UpdateLoadElement(DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1181 const KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode) {
1182 Handle<Map> receiver_map(receiver->map(), isolate());
1183 DCHECK(receiver_map->instance_type() !=
1184 JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE); // Checked by caller.
1185 MapHandles target_receiver_maps;
1186 TargetMaps(&target_receiver_maps);
1187
1188 if (target_receiver_maps.empty()) {
1189 Handle<Object> handler = LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1190 return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1191 }
1192
1193 for (DirectHandle<Map> map : target_receiver_maps) {
1194 if (map.is_null()) continue;
1195 if (map->instance_type() == JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE) {
1196 set_slow_stub_reason("JSPrimitiveWrapper");
1197 return;
1198 }
1199 if (map->instance_type() == JS_PROXY_TYPE) {
1200 set_slow_stub_reason("JSProxy");
1201 return;
1202 }
1203 }
1204
1205 // The first time a receiver is seen that is a transitioned version of the
1206 // previous monomorphic receiver type, assume the new ElementsKind is the
1207 // monomorphic type. This benefits global arrays that only transition
1208 // once, and all call sites accessing them are faster if they remain
1209 // monomorphic. If this optimistic assumption is not true, the IC will
1210 // miss again and it will become polymorphic and support both the
1211 // untransitioned and transitioned maps.
1212 if (state() == MONOMORPHIC) {
1213 if ((IsJSObject(*receiver) &&
1214 IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
1215 target_receiver_maps.at(0)->elements_kind(),
1216 Cast<JSObject>(receiver)->GetElementsKind())) ||
1217 IsWasmObject(*receiver)) {
1218 Handle<Object> handler = LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1219 return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1220 }
1221 }
1222
1223 DCHECK(state() != GENERIC);
1224
1225 // Determine the list of receiver maps that this call site has seen,
1226 // adding the map that was just encountered.
1227 KeyedAccessLoadMode old_load_mode = KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1228 if (!AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_receiver_maps, receiver_map)) {
1229 old_load_mode = GetKeyedAccessLoadModeFor(receiver_map);
1230 if (!AllowedHandlerChange(old_load_mode, new_load_mode)) {
1231 set_slow_stub_reason("same map added twice");
1232 return;
1233 }
1234 }
1235
1236 // If the maximum number of receiver maps has been exceeded, use the generic
1237 // version of the IC.
1238 if (static_cast<int>(target_receiver_maps.size()) >
1239 v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
1240 set_slow_stub_reason("max polymorph exceeded");
1241 return;
1242 }
1243
1244 MaybeObjectHandles handlers;
1245 handlers.reserve(target_receiver_maps.size());
1246 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode =
1247 GeneralizeKeyedAccessLoadMode(old_load_mode, new_load_mode);
1248 LoadElementPolymorphicHandlers(&target_receiver_maps, &handlers, load_mode);
1249 if (target_receiver_maps.empty()) {
1250 Handle<Object> handler = LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1251 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1252 } else if (target_receiver_maps.size() == 1) {
1253 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), target_receiver_maps[0],
1254 handlers[0]);
1255 } else {
1256 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(),
1257 MapHandlesSpan(target_receiver_maps.begin(),
1258 target_receiver_maps.end()),
1259 &handlers);
1260 }
1261}
1262
1263namespace {
1264
1265bool AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(Isolate* isolate,
1266 DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map) {
1267 if (IsJSTypedArrayMap(*receiver_map)) {
1268 // For JSTypedArray we never lookup elements in the prototype chain.
1269 return true;
1270 }
1271
1272 // For other {receiver}s we need to check the "no elements" protector.
1273 if (Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate)) {
1274 if (IsStringMap(*receiver_map)) {
1275 return true;
1276 }
1277 if (IsJSObjectMap(*receiver_map)) {
1278 // For other JSObjects (including JSArrays) we can only continue if
1279 // the {receiver}s prototype is either the initial Object.prototype
1280 // or the initial Array.prototype, which are both guarded by the
1281 // "no elements" protector checked above.
1282 DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver_prototype(receiver_map->prototype(),
1283 isolate);
1284 InstanceType prototype_type = receiver_prototype->map()->instance_type();
1285 if (prototype_type == JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE ||
1286 (prototype_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE &&
1287 isolate->IsInCreationContext(
1288 Cast<JSObject>(*receiver_prototype),
1289 Context::INITIAL_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_INDEX))) {
1290 return true;
1291 }
1292 }
1293 }
1294
1295 return false;
1296}
1297
1298bool IsOutOfBoundsAccess(DirectHandle<Object> receiver, size_t index) {
1299 size_t length;
1300 if (IsJSArray(*receiver)) {
1301 length = Object::NumberValue(Cast<JSArray>(*receiver)->length());
1302 } else if (IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1303 length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*receiver)->GetLength();
1304 } else if (IsJSObject(*receiver)) {
1305 length = Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->elements()->length();
1306 } else if (IsString(*receiver)) {
1307 length = Cast<String>(*receiver)->length();
1308 } else {
1309 return false;
1310 }
1311 return index >= length;
1312}
1313
1314bool AllowReadingHoleElement(ElementsKind elements_kind) {
1315 return IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind);
1316}
1317
1318KeyedAccessLoadMode GetNewKeyedLoadMode(Isolate* isolate,
1319 DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1320 size_t index, bool is_found) {
1321 DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map(Cast<HeapObject>(receiver)->map(), isolate);
1322 if (!AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate, receiver_map)) {
1323 return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1324 }
1325
1326 // Always handle holes when the elements kind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS, since the
1327 // optimizer compilers can not benefit from this information to narrow the
1328 // type. That is, the load type will always just be a generic tagged value.
1329 // This avoid an IC miss if we see a hole.
1330 ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
1331 bool always_handle_holes = (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
1332
1333 // In bound access and did not read a hole.
1334 if (is_found) {
1335 return always_handle_holes ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1336 : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1337 }
1338
1339 // OOB access.
1340 bool is_oob_access = IsOutOfBoundsAccess(receiver, index);
1341 if (is_oob_access) {
1342 return always_handle_holes ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles
1343 : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB;
1344 }
1345
1346 // Read a hole.
1347 DCHECK(!is_found && !is_oob_access);
1348 bool handle_hole = AllowReadingHoleElement(elements_kind);
1349 DCHECK_IMPLIES(always_handle_holes, handle_hole);
1350 return handle_hole ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1351 : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1352}
1353
1354KeyedAccessLoadMode GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap(Isolate* isolate,
1355 DirectHandle<Map> map,
1356 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
1357 // If we are not allowed to convert a hole to undefined, then we should not
1358 // handle OOB nor reading holes.
1359 if (!AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate, map)) {
1360 return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1361 }
1362 // Check if the elements kind allow reading a hole.
1363 bool allow_reading_hole_element =
1364 AllowReadingHoleElement(map->elements_kind());
1365 switch (load_mode) {
1366 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds:
1367 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB:
1368 return load_mode;
1369 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles:
1370 return allow_reading_hole_element ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1371 : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1372 case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles:
1373 return allow_reading_hole_element
1374 ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles
1375 : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB;
1376 }
1377}
1378
1379} // namespace
1380
1381Handle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementHandler(
1382 DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map, KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode) {
1383 // Has a getter interceptor, or is any has and has a query interceptor.
1384 if (receiver_map->has_indexed_interceptor() &&
1385 (!IsUndefined(receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->getter(),
1386 isolate()) ||
1387 (IsAnyHas() &&
1388 !IsUndefined(receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->query(),
1389 isolate()))) &&
1390 !receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->non_masking()) {
1391 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1392 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadIndexedInterceptorStub);
1393 return IsAnyHas() ? BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), HasIndexedInterceptorIC)
1394 : BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIndexedInterceptorIC);
1395 }
1396
1397 InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map->instance_type();
1398 if (instance_type < FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE) {
1399 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadIndexedStringDH);
1400 if (IsAnyHas()) return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1401 return LoadHandler::LoadIndexedString(isolate(), new_load_mode);
1402 }
1403 if (instance_type < FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE) {
1404 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SlowStub);
1405 return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1406 }
1407 if (instance_type == JS_PROXY_TYPE) {
1408 return LoadHandler::LoadProxy(isolate());
1409 }
1410#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1411 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsWasmObject(instance_type)) {
1412 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1413 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SlowStub);
1414 return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1415 }
1416#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1417
1418 ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
1419 if (IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
1420 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1421 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_KeyedLoadSloppyArgumentsStub);
1422 return IsAnyHas() ? BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), KeyedHasIC_SloppyArguments)
1423 : BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SloppyArguments);
1424 }
1425 bool is_js_array = instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE;
1426 if (elements_kind == DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS) {
1427 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadElementDH);
1428 return LoadHandler::LoadElement(isolate(), elements_kind, is_js_array,
1429 new_load_mode);
1430 }
1431 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
1432 IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
1433 IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
1434 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1435 LoadModeHandlesHoles(new_load_mode),
1436 AllowReadingHoleElement(elements_kind) &&
1437 AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate(), receiver_map));
1438 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadElementDH);
1439 return LoadHandler::LoadElement(isolate(), elements_kind, is_js_array,
1440 new_load_mode);
1441}
1442
1443void KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementPolymorphicHandlers(
1444 MapHandles* receiver_maps, MaybeObjectHandles* handlers,
1445 KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode) {
1446 // Filter out deprecated maps to ensure their instances get migrated.
1447 receiver_maps->erase(std::remove_if(
1448 receiver_maps->begin(), receiver_maps->end(),
1449 [](const DirectHandle<Map>& map) { return map->is_deprecated(); }));
1450
1451 for (DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map : *receiver_maps) {
1452 // Mark all stable receiver maps that have elements kind transition map
1453 // among receiver_maps as unstable because the optimizing compilers may
1454 // generate an elements kind transition for this kind of receivers.
1455 if (receiver_map->is_stable()) {
1456 Tagged<Map> tmap = receiver_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
1457 isolate(),
1458 MapHandlesSpan(receiver_maps->begin(), receiver_maps->end()),
1459 ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
1460 if (!tmap.is_null()) {
1461 receiver_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
1462 }
1463 }
1464 handlers->push_back(MaybeObjectHandle(LoadElementHandler(
1465 receiver_map,
1466 GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap(isolate(), receiver_map, new_load_mode))));
1467 }
1468}
1469
1470namespace {
1471
1472enum KeyType { kIntPtr, kName, kBailout };
1473
1474// The cases where kIntPtr is returned must match what
1475// CodeStubAssembler::TryToIntptr can handle!
1476KeyType TryConvertKey(Handle<Object> key, Isolate* isolate, intptr_t* index_out,
1477 Handle<Name>* name_out) {
1478 if (IsSmi(*key)) {
1479 *index_out = Smi::ToInt(*key);
1480 return kIntPtr;
1481 }
1482 if (IsHeapNumber(*key)) {
1483 double num = Cast<HeapNumber>(*key)->value();
1484 if (!(num >= -kMaxSafeInteger)) return kBailout;
1485 if (num > kMaxSafeInteger) return kBailout;
1486 *index_out = static_cast<intptr_t>(num);
1487 if (*index_out != num) return kBailout;
1488 return kIntPtr;
1489 }
1490 if (IsString(*key)) {
1491 key = isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(Cast<String>(key));
1492 uint32_t maybe_array_index;
1493 if (Cast<String>(*key)->AsArrayIndex(&maybe_array_index)) {
1494 if (maybe_array_index <= INT_MAX) {
1495 *index_out = static_cast<intptr_t>(maybe_array_index);
1496 return kIntPtr;
1497 }
1498 // {key} is a string representation of an array index beyond the range
1499 // that the IC could handle. Don't try to take the named-property path.
1500 return kBailout;
1501 }
1502 *name_out = Cast<String>(key);
1503 return kName;
1504 }
1505 if (IsSymbol(*key)) {
1506 *name_out = Cast<Symbol>(key);
1507 return kName;
1508 }
1509 return kBailout;
1510}
1511
1512bool IntPtrKeyToSize(intptr_t index, DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1513 size_t* out) {
1514 if (index < 0) {
1515 if (IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1516 // For JSTypedArray receivers, we can support negative keys, which we
1517 // just map to a very large value. This is valid because all OOB accesses
1518 // (negative or positive) are handled the same way, and size_t::max is
1519 // guaranteed to be an OOB access.
1520 *out = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
1521 return true;
1522 }
1523 return false;
1524 }
1525#if V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT
1526 if (index > JSObject::kMaxElementIndex && !IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1527 return false;
1528 }
1529#else
1530 // On 32-bit platforms, any intptr_t is less than kMaxElementIndex.
1531 static_assert(
1532 static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<decltype(index)>::max()) <=
1533 static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex));
1534#endif
1535 *out = static_cast<size_t>(index);
1536 return true;
1537}
1538
1539bool CanCache(DirectHandle<Object> receiver, InlineCacheState state) {
1540 if (!v8_flags.use_ic || state == NO_FEEDBACK) return false;
1541 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver) && !IsString(*receiver)) return false;
1542 return !IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) && !IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*receiver);
1543}

1545} // namespace
