1547MaybeHandle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::RuntimeLoad(DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
1548 DirectHandle<Object> key,
1549 bool* is_found) {
1550 Handle<Object> result;
1551
1552 if (IsKeyedLoadIC()) {
1553 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1554 isolate(), result,
1555 Runtime::GetObjectProperty(isolate(), object, key,
1556 DirectHandle<JSAny>(), is_found));
1557 } else {
1558 DCHECK(IsKeyedHasIC());
1559 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
1560 Runtime::HasProperty(isolate(), object, key));
1561 }
1562 return result;
1563}
1564
1565MaybeHandle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::LoadName(Handle<JSAny> object,
1566 DirectHandle<Object> key,
1567 Handle<Name> name) {
1568 Handle<Object> load_handle;
1569 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), load_handle,
1570 LoadIC::Load(object, name));
1571
1572 if (vector_needs_update()) {
1573 ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key);
1574 TraceIC("LoadIC", key);
1575 }
1576
1577 DCHECK(!load_handle.is_null());
1578 return load_handle;
1579}
1580
1581MaybeHandle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::Load(Handle<JSAny> object,
1582 Handle<Object> key) {
1583 if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
1584 return RuntimeLoad(object, key);
1585 }
1586
1587 intptr_t maybe_index;
1588 Handle<Name> maybe_name;
1589 KeyType key_type = TryConvertKey(key, isolate(), &maybe_index, &maybe_name);
1590
1591 if (key_type == kName) return LoadName(object, key, maybe_name);
1592
1593 bool is_found = false;
1594 MaybeHandle<Object> result = RuntimeLoad(object, key, &is_found);
1595
1596 size_t index;
1597 if (key_type == kIntPtr && CanCache(object, state()) &&
1598 IntPtrKeyToSize(maybe_index, Cast<HeapObject>(object), &index)) {
1599 DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
1600 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode =
1601 GetNewKeyedLoadMode(isolate(), receiver, index, is_found);
1602 UpdateLoadElement(receiver, load_mode);
1603 if (is_vector_set()) {
1604 TraceIC("LoadIC", key);
1605 }
1606 }
1607
1608 if (vector_needs_update()) {
1609 ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key);
1610 TraceIC("LoadIC", key);
1611 }
1612
1613 return result;
1614}
1615
1616bool StoreIC::LookupForWrite(LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1617 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1618 // Disable ICs for non-JSObjects for now.
1619 DirectHandle<Object> object = it->GetReceiver();
1620 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) return true;
1621 if (!IsJSObject(*object)) return false;
1622 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(object);
1623 DCHECK(!receiver->map()->is_deprecated());
1624
1625 for (;; it->Next()) {
1626 switch (it->state()) {
1627 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1628 UNREACHABLE();
1629 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1630 return false;
1631 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
1632 return true;
1633 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
1634 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1635 Tagged<InterceptorInfo> info = holder->GetNamedInterceptor();
1636 if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype() ||
1637 !IsUndefined(info->getter(), isolate()) ||
1638 !IsUndefined(info->query(), isolate())) {
1639 return true;
1640 }
1641 continue;
1642 }
1643 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1644 if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*it->GetHolder<JSObject>())) return false;
1645 continue;
1646 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1647 return !it->IsReadOnly();
1648 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1649 return false;
1650 case LookupIterator::DATA: {
1651 if (it->IsReadOnly()) return false;
1652 if (IsAnyDefineOwn() && it->property_attributes() != NONE) {
1653 // IC doesn't support reconfiguration of property attributes,
1654 // so just bail out to the slow handler.
1655 return false;
1656 }
1657 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1658 if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
1659 it->PrepareForDataProperty(value);
1660 // The previous receiver map might just have been deprecated,
1661 // so reload it.
1662 update_lookup_start_object_map(receiver);
1663 return true;
1664 }
1665
1666 // Receiver != holder.
1667 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) {
1668 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate(), receiver);
1669 return it->GetHolder<Object>().is_identical_to(
1670 PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter));
1671 }
1672
1673 if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) return false;
1674
1675 if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) return false;
1676 it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, NONE,
1677 store_origin);
1678 return it->IsCacheableTransition();
1679 }
1680 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1681 // If we are in StoreGlobal then check if we should throw on
1682 // non-existent properties.
1683 if (IsStoreGlobalIC() &&
1684 (GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), Nothing<ShouldThrow>()) ==
1685 ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)) {
1686 // ICs typically does the store in two steps: prepare receiver for the
1687 // transition followed by the actual store. For global objects we
1688 // create a property cell when preparing for transition and install
1689 // this cell in the handler. In strict mode, we throw and never
1690 // initialize this property cell. The IC handler assumes that the
1691 // property cell it is holding is for a property that is existing.
1692 // This case violates this assumption. If we happen to invalidate this
1693 // property cell later, it leads to incorrect behaviour. For now just
1694 // use a slow stub and don't install the property cell for these
1695 // cases. Hopefully these cases are not frequent enough to impact
1696 // performance.
1697 //
1698 // TODO(mythria): If we find this to be happening often, we could
1699 // install a new kind of handler for non-existent properties. These
1700 // handlers can then miss to runtime if the value is not hole (i.e.
1701 // cell got invalidated) and handle these stores correctly.
1702 return false;
1703 }
1704 receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSObject>();
1705 if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) return false;
1706 it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, NONE,
1707 store_origin);
1708 return it->IsCacheableTransition();
1709 }
1710 UNREACHABLE();
1711 }
1712}
1713
1714MaybeHandle<Object> StoreGlobalIC::Store(Handle<Name> name,
1715 Handle<Object> value) {
1716 DCHECK(IsString(*name));
1717
1718 // Look up in script context table.
1719 DirectHandle<String> str_name = Cast<String>(name);
1720 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global = isolate()->global_object();
1721 DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
1722 global->native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
1723
1724 VariableLookupResult lookup_result;
1725 if (script_contexts->Lookup(str_name, &lookup_result)) {
1726 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1727 DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
1728 Tagged<Context> script_context =
1729 script_contexts->get(lookup_result.context_index);
1730 if (IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode)) {
1731 AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1732 return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kConstAssign, global, name);
1733 }
1734
1735 Tagged<Object> previous_value =
1736 script_context->get(lookup_result.slot_index);
1737
1738 if (IsTheHole(previous_value, isolate())) {
1739 // Do not install stubs and stay pre-monomorphic for uninitialized
1740 // accesses.
1741 AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1742 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1743 isolate(),
1744 NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kAccessedUninitializedVariable,
1745 name));
1746 }
1747
1748 bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic;
1749 if (use_ic) {
1750 if (nexus()->ConfigureLexicalVarMode(
1751 lookup_result.context_index, lookup_result.slot_index,
1752 IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode))) {
1753 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreGlobalIC_StoreScriptContextField);
1754 } else {
1755 // Given combination of indices can't be encoded, so use slow stub.
1756 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreGlobalIC_SlowStub);
1757 SetCache(name, StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1758 }
1759 TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name);
1760 } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
1761 TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name);
1762 }
1763 if (v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number ||
1764 v8_flags.const_tracking_let) {
1765 AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1766 Context::StoreScriptContextAndUpdateSlotProperty(
1767 direct_handle(script_context, isolate()), lookup_result.slot_index,
1768 value, isolate());
1769 } else {
1770 script_context->set(lookup_result.slot_index, *value);
1771 }
1772 return value;
1773 }
1774
1775 return StoreIC::Store(global, name, value);
1776}
1777
1778namespace {
1779Maybe<bool> DefineOwnDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
1780 LookupIterator::State original_state,
1781 DirectHandle<JSAny> value,
1782 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
1783 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1784 // It should not be possible to call DefineOwnDataProperty in a
1785 // contextual store (indicated by IsJSGlobalObject()).
1786 DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*it->GetReceiver(), it->isolate()));
1787
1788 // Handle special cases that can't be handled by
1789 // DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes first.
1790 switch (it->state()) {
1791 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1792 PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1793 new_desc.set_value(value);
1794 new_desc.set_writable(true);
1795 new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1796 new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1797 DCHECK_EQ(original_state, LookupIterator::JSPROXY);
1798 // TODO(joyee): this will start the lookup again. Ideally we should
1799 // implement something that reuses the existing LookupIterator.
1800 return JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1801 it->GetName(), &new_desc, should_throw);
1802 }
1803 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1804 RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
1805 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1806 // When lazy feedback is disabled, the original state could be different
1807 // while the object is already prepared for TRANSITION.
1808 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION: {
1809 switch (original_state) {
1810 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
1811 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1812 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1813 case LookupIterator::DATA:
1814 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1815 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1816 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1817 UNREACHABLE();
1818 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
1819 DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
1820 [[fallthrough]];
1821 }
1822 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1823 return Object::AddDataProperty(it, value, NONE,
1824 Nothing<ShouldThrow>(), store_origin,
1825 EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine);
1826 }
1827 }
1828 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1829 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1830 case LookupIterator::DATA:
1831 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1832 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1833 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1834 break;
1835 }
1836
1837 // We need to restart to handle interceptors properly.
1838 it->Restart();
1839
1840 return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
1841 it, value, NONE, should_throw, JSObject::DONT_FORCE_FIELD,
1842 EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine, store_origin);
1843}
1844} // namespace
1845
1846MaybeHandle<Object> StoreIC::Store(Handle<JSAny> object, Handle<Name> name,
1847 Handle<Object> value,
1848 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1849 // TODO(verwaest): Let SetProperty do the migration, since storing a property
1850 // might deprecate the current map again, if value does not fit.
1851 if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
1852 // KeyedStoreIC should handle DefineKeyedOwnIC with deprecated maps directly
1853 // instead of reusing this method.
1854 DCHECK(!IsDefineKeyedOwnIC());
1855 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivateName());
1856
1857 PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
1858 if (IsDefineNamedOwnIC()) {
1859 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
1860 isolate(), object, key, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()));
1861 } else {
1862 LookupIterator it(isolate(), object, key, LookupIterator::DEFAULT);
1863 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kNamed));
1864 }
1865 return value;
1866 }
1867
1868 bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic;
1869 // If the object is undefined or null it's illegal to try to set any
1870 // properties on it; throw a TypeError in that case.
1871 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate())) {
1872 if (use_ic) {
1873 // Ensure the IC state progresses.
1874 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_NonReceiver);
1875 update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
1876 SetCache(name, StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1877 TraceIC("StoreIC", name);
1878 }
1879 return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectPropertyStoreWithProperty, name,
1880 object);
1881 }
1882
1883 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtPrototype, isolate());
1884 PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
1885 LookupIterator it(
1886 isolate(), object, key,
1887 IsAnyDefineOwn() ? LookupIterator::OWN : LookupIterator::DEFAULT);
1888
1889 if (name->IsPrivate()) {
1890 if (name->IsPrivateName()) {
1891 DCHECK(!IsDefineNamedOwnIC());
1892 Maybe<bool> can_store =
1893 JSReceiver::CheckPrivateNameStore(&it, IsDefineKeyedOwnIC());
1894 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_store);
1895 if (!can_store.FromJust()) {
1896 return isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1897 }
1898 }
1899
1900 // IC handling of private fields/symbols stores on JSProxy is not
1901 // supported.
1902 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
1903 use_ic = false;
1904 }
1905 }
1906
1907 // For IsAnyDefineOwn(), we can't simply do CreateDataProperty below
1908 // because we need to check the attributes before UpdateCaches updates
1909 // the state of the LookupIterator.
1910 LookupIterator::State original_state = it.state();
1911 // We'll defer the check for JSProxy and objects with named interceptors,
1912 // because the defineProperty traps need to be called first if they are
1913 // present. We can also skip this for private names since they are not
1914 // bound by configurability or extensibility checks, and errors would've
1915 // been thrown if the private field already exists in the object.
1916 if (IsAnyDefineOwn() && !name->IsPrivateName() && IsJSObject(*object) &&
1917 !Cast<JSObject>(object)->HasNamedInterceptor()) {
1918 Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
1919 isolate(), &it, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
1920 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_define);
1921 if (!can_define.FromJust()) {
1922 return isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1923 }
1924 // Restart the lookup iterator updated by CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable()
1925 // for UpdateCaches() to handle access checks.
1926 if (use_ic && IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object)) {
1927 it.Restart();
1928 }
1929 }
1930
1931 if (use_ic) {
1932 UpdateCaches(&it, value, store_origin);
1933 } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
1934 // Tracing IC Stats for No Feedback State.
1935 IsStoreGlobalIC() ? TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name)
1936 : TraceIC("StoreIC", name);
1937 }
1938
1939 // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefinedNamedOwnIC and SetNamedIC as subclasses
1940 // of StoreIC so their logic doesn't get mixed here.
1941 // ES #sec-definefield
1942 // ES #sec-runtime-semantics-propertydefinitionevaluation
1943 // IsAnyDefineOwn() can be true when this method is reused by KeyedStoreIC.
1944 if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1945 if (name->IsPrivateName()) {
1946 // We should define private fields without triggering traps or checking
1947 // extensibility.
1948 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(
1949 JSReceiver::AddPrivateField(&it, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()));
1950 } else {
1951 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(
1952 DefineOwnDataProperty(&it, original_state, Cast<JSAny>(value),
1953 Nothing<ShouldThrow>(), store_origin));
1954 }
1955 } else {
1956 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, store_origin));
1957 }
1958 return value;
1959}
1960
1961void StoreIC::UpdateCaches(LookupIterator* lookup, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1962 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1963 MaybeObjectHandle handler;
1964 if (LookupForWrite(lookup, value, store_origin)) {
1965 if (IsStoreGlobalIC()) {
1966 if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
1967 lookup->GetReceiver().is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<Object>())) {
1968 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup->GetReceiver()));
1969 // Now update the cell in the feedback vector.
1970 nexus()->ConfigurePropertyCellMode(lookup->GetPropertyCell());
1971 TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", lookup->GetName());
1972 return;
1973 }
1974 }
1975 handler = ComputeHandler(lookup);
1976 } else {
1977 set_slow_stub_reason("LookupForWrite said 'false'");
1978 handler = MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1979 }
1980 // Can't use {lookup->name()} because the LookupIterator might be in
1981 // "elements" mode for keys that are strings representing integers above
1982 // JSArray::kMaxIndex.
1983 SetCache(lookup->GetName(), handler);
1984 TraceIC("StoreIC", lookup->GetName());
1985}
1986
1987MaybeObjectHandle StoreIC::ComputeHandler(LookupIterator* lookup) {
1988 switch (lookup->state()) {
1989 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION: {
1990 Handle<JSObject> store_target =
1991 indirect_handle(lookup->GetStoreTarget<JSObject>(), isolate());
1992 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*store_target)) {
1993 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreGlobalTransitionDH);
1994
1995 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup_start_object_map())) {
1996 DCHECK(IsStoreGlobalIC());
1997#ifdef DEBUG
1998 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1999 DCHECK_EQ(*lookup->GetReceiver(), *holder);
2000 DCHECK_EQ(*store_target, *holder);
2001#endif
2002 return StoreHandler::StoreGlobal(
2003 indirect_handle(lookup->transition_cell(), isolate()));
2004 }
2005 if (IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2006 // Private field can't be deleted from this global object and can't
2007 // be overwritten, so install slow handler in order to make store IC
2008 // throw if a private name already exists.
2009 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2010 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2011 }
2012
2013 DirectHandle<Smi> smi_handler =
2014 StoreHandler::StoreGlobalProxy(isolate());
2015 Handle<Object> handler = StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2016 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), store_target, *smi_handler,
2017 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
2018 indirect_handle(lookup->transition_cell(), isolate())));
2019 return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2020 }
2021 // Dictionary-to-fast transitions are not expected and not supported.
2022 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!lookup->transition_map()->is_dictionary_map(),
2023 !lookup_start_object_map()->is_dictionary_map());
2024
2025 DCHECK(lookup->IsCacheableTransition());
2026 if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2027 return StoreHandler::StoreOwnTransition(
2028 isolate(), indirect_handle(lookup->transition_map(), isolate()));
2029 }
2030 return StoreHandler::StoreTransition(
2031 isolate(), indirect_handle(lookup->transition_map(), isolate()));
2032 }
2033
2034 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
2035 Handle<JSObject> holder =
2036 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
2037 Tagged<InterceptorInfo> info = holder->GetNamedInterceptor();
2038
2039 // If the interceptor is on the receiver...
2040 if (lookup->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype() && !info->non_masking()) {
2041 // ...return a store interceptor Smi handler if there is a setter
2042 // interceptor and it's not DefineNamedOwnIC or DefineKeyedOwnIC
2043 // (which should call the definer)...
2044 if (!IsUndefined(info->setter(), isolate()) && !IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2045 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreInterceptor(isolate()));
2046 }
2047 // ...otherwise return a slow-case Smi handler, which invokes the
2048 // definer for DefineNamedOwnIC.
2049 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2050 }
2051
2052 // If the interceptor is a getter/query interceptor on the prototype
2053 // chain, return an invalidatable slow handler so it can turn fast if the
2054 // interceptor is masked by a regular property later.
2055 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(info->getter(), isolate()) ||
2056 !IsUndefined(info->query(), isolate()));
2057 Handle<Object> handler = StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2058 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder,
2059 *StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2060 return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2061 }
2062
2063 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
2064 // This is currently guaranteed by checks in StoreIC::Store.
2065 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2066 Handle<JSObject> holder =
2067 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
2068 DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) || lookup->name()->IsPrivate());
2069
2070 if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2071 set_slow_stub_reason("define own with existing accessor");
2072 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2073 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2074 }
2075 if (!holder->HasFastProperties()) {
2076 set_slow_stub_reason("accessor on slow map");
2077 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2078 MaybeObjectHandle handler =
2079 MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2080 return handler;
2081 }
2082 DirectHandle<Object> accessors = lookup->GetAccessors();
2083 if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors)) {
2084 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(accessors);
2085 if (!info->has_setter(isolate())) {
2086 set_slow_stub_reason("setter == kNullAddress");
2087 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2088 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2089 }
2090 if (!lookup->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2091 set_slow_stub_reason("native data property in prototype chain");
2092 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2093 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2094 }
2095
2096 Handle<Smi> smi_handler = StoreHandler::StoreNativeDataProperty(
2097 isolate(), lookup->GetAccessorIndex());
2098 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreNativeDataPropertyDH);
2099 if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
2100 return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
2101 }
2102 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
2103 StoreIC_StoreNativeDataPropertyOnPrototypeDH);
2104 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2105 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, *smi_handler));
2106
2107 } else if (IsAccessorPair(*accessors)) {
2108 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair =
2109 Cast<AccessorPair>(accessors);
2110 Handle<Object> setter(accessor_pair->setter(), isolate());
2111 if (!IsCallableJSFunction(*setter) &&
2112 !IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
2113 set_slow_stub_reason("setter not a function");
2114 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2115 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2116 }
2117
2118 if ((IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter) &&
2119 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*setter)->BreakAtEntry(isolate())) ||
2120 (IsJSFunction(*setter) &&
2121 Cast<JSFunction>(*setter)->shared()->BreakAtEntry(isolate()))) {
2122 // Do not install an IC if the api function has a breakpoint.
2123 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2124 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2125 }
2126
2127 CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), setter);
2128 if (call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) {
2129 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
2130 DirectHandle<JSObject> api_holder =
2131 call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
2132 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), &holder_lookup);
2133 if (call_optimization.IsCompatibleReceiverMap(api_holder, holder,
2134 holder_lookup)) {
2135 DirectHandle<Smi> smi_handler = StoreHandler::StoreApiSetter(
2136 isolate(),
2137 holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
2138
2139 Handle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
2140 GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, holder->map(), isolate());
2141
2142 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreApiSetterOnPrototypeDH);
2143 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2144 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, *smi_handler,
2145 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(call_optimization.api_call_info()),
2146 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(accessor_context)));
2147 }
2148 set_slow_stub_reason("incompatible receiver");
2149 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2150 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2151 } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
2152 set_slow_stub_reason("setter non-simple template");
2153 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2154 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2155 }
2156
2157 DCHECK(IsCallableJSFunction(*setter));
2158 if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
2159 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreAccessorDH);
2160 return MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
2161 indirect_handle(accessor_pair, isolate()));
2162 }
2163 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreAccessorOnPrototypeDH);
2164
2165 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2166 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder,
2167 *StoreHandler::StoreAccessorFromPrototype(isolate()),
2168 MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(setter)));
2169 }
2170 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2171 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2172 }
2173
2174 case LookupIterator::DATA: {
2175 // This is currently guaranteed by checks in StoreIC::Store.
2176 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2177 USE(receiver);
2178 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2179 DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) || lookup->name()->IsPrivate());
2180
2181 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, lookup->property_details().kind());
2182 if (lookup->is_dictionary_holder()) {
2183 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder)) {
2184 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreGlobalDH);
2185 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreGlobal(
2186 indirect_handle(lookup->GetPropertyCell(), isolate())));
2187 }
2188 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreNormalDH);
2189 DCHECK(holder.is_identical_to(receiver));
2190 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
2191 lookup->constness() == PropertyConstness::kMutable);
2192
2193 Handle<Smi> handler = StoreHandler::StoreNormal(isolate());
2194 return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2195 }
2196
2197 // -------------- Elements (for TypedArrays) -------------
2198 if (lookup->IsElement(*holder)) {
2199 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2200 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2201 }
2202
2203 // -------------- Fields --------------
2204 if (lookup->property_details().location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
2205 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreFieldDH);
2206 int descriptor = lookup->GetFieldDescriptorIndex();
2207 FieldIndex index = lookup->GetFieldIndex();
2208 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsJSSharedStruct(*holder))) {
2209 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSharedStructField(
2210 isolate(), descriptor, index, lookup->representation()));
2211 }
2212 PropertyConstness constness = lookup->constness();
2213 if (constness == PropertyConstness::kConst &&
2214 IsDefineNamedOwnICKind(nexus()->kind())) {
2215 // DefineNamedOwnICs are used for initializing object literals
2216 // therefore we must store the value unconditionally even to
2217 // VariableMode::kConst fields.
2218 constness = PropertyConstness::kMutable;
2219 }
2220 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreField(
2221 isolate(), descriptor, index, constness, lookup->representation()));
2222 }
2223
2224 // -------------- Constant properties --------------
2225 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor,
2226 lookup->property_details().location());
2227 set_slow_stub_reason("constant property");
2228 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2229 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2230 }
2231 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2232 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver =
2233 Cast<JSReceiver>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2234 Handle<JSProxy> holder =
2235 indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), isolate());
2236
2237 // IsDefineNamedOwnIC() is true when we are defining public fields on a
2238 // Proxy. IsDefineKeyedOwnIC() is true when we are defining computed
2239 // fields in a Proxy. In these cases use the slow stub to invoke the
2240 // define trap.
2241 if (IsDefineNamedOwnIC() || IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2242 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2243 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2244 }
2245
2246 return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreProxy(
2247 isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, receiver));
2248 }
2249
2250 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
2251 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2252 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2253 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2254 UNREACHABLE();
2255 }
2256 return MaybeObjectHandle();
2257}
2258
2259void KeyedStoreIC::UpdateStoreElement(Handle<Map> receiver_map,
2260 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode,
2261 Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
2262 MapsAndHandlers target_maps_and_handlers;
2263 nexus()->ExtractMapsAndHandlers(
2264 &target_maps_and_handlers,
2265 [this](Handle<Map> map) { return Map::TryUpdate(isolate(), map); });
2266 if (target_maps_and_handlers.empty()) {
2267 DirectHandle<Map> monomorphic_map = receiver_map;
2268 // If we transitioned to a map that is a more general map than incoming
2269 // then use the new map.
2270 if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*receiver_map, *new_receiver_map)) {
2271 monomorphic_map = new_receiver_map;
2272 }
2273 Handle<Object> handler = StoreElementHandler(monomorphic_map, store_mode);
2274 return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), monomorphic_map, handler);
2275 }
2276
2277 for (const MapAndHandler& map_and_handler : target_maps_and_handlers) {
2278 DirectHandle<Map> map = map_and_handler.first;
2279 if (!map.is_null() && map->instance_type() == JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE) {
2280 DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2281 set_slow_stub_reason("JSPrimitiveWrapper");
2282 return;
2283 }
2284 }
2285
2286 // There are several special cases where an IC that is MONOMORPHIC can still
2287 // transition to a different IC that handles a superset of the original IC.
2288 // Handle those here if the receiver map hasn't changed or it has transitioned
2289 // to a more general kind.
2290 KeyedAccessStoreMode old_store_mode = GetKeyedAccessStoreMode();
2291 Handle<Map> previous_receiver_map = target_maps_and_handlers.at(0).first;
2292 if (state() == MONOMORPHIC) {
2293 DirectHandle<Map> transitioned_receiver_map = new_receiver_map;
2294 if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*previous_receiver_map,
2295 *transitioned_receiver_map)) {
2296 // If the "old" and "new" maps are in the same elements map family, or
2297 // if they at least come from the same origin for a transitioning store,
2298 // stay MONOMORPHIC and use the map for the most generic ElementsKind.
2299 Handle<Object> handler =
2300 StoreElementHandler(transitioned_receiver_map, store_mode);
2301 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), transitioned_receiver_map,
2302 handler);
2303 return;
2304 }
2305 // If there is no transition and if we have seen the same map earlier and
2306 // there is only a change in the store_mode we can still stay monomorphic.
2307 if (receiver_map.is_identical_to(previous_receiver_map) &&
2308 new_receiver_map.is_identical_to(receiver_map) &&
2309 StoreModeIsInBounds(old_store_mode) &&
2310 !StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2311 if (IsJSArrayMap(*receiver_map) &&
2312 JSArray::MayHaveReadOnlyLength(*receiver_map)) {
2313 set_slow_stub_reason(
2314 "can't generalize store mode (potentially read-only length)");
2315 return;
2316 }
2317 // A "normal" IC that handles stores can switch to a version that can
2318 // grow at the end of the array, handle OOB accesses or copy COW arrays
2319 // and still stay MONOMORPHIC.
2320 Handle<Object> handler = StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode);
2321 return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 DCHECK(state() != GENERIC);
2326
2327 bool map_added =
2328 AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_maps_and_handlers, receiver_map);
2329
2330 if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*receiver_map, *new_receiver_map)) {
2331 map_added |=
2332 AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_maps_and_handlers, new_receiver_map);
2333 }
2334
2335 if (!map_added) {
2336 // If the miss wasn't due to an unseen map, a polymorphic stub
2337 // won't help, use the megamorphic stub which can handle everything.
2338 set_slow_stub_reason("same map added twice");
2339 return;
2340 }
2341
2342 // If the maximum number of receiver maps has been exceeded, use the
2343 // megamorphic version of the IC.
2344 if (static_cast<int>(target_maps_and_handlers.size()) >
2345 v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
2346 return;
2347 }
2348
2349 // Make sure all polymorphic handlers have the same store mode, otherwise the
2350 // megamorphic stub must be used.
2351 if (!StoreModeIsInBounds(old_store_mode)) {
2352 if (StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2353 store_mode = old_store_mode;
2354 } else if (store_mode != old_store_mode) {
2355 set_slow_stub_reason("store mode mismatch");
2356 return;
2357 }
2358 }
2359
2360 // If the store mode isn't the standard mode, make sure that all polymorphic
2361 // receivers are either external arrays, or all "normal" arrays with writable
2362 // length. Otherwise, use the megamorphic stub.
2363 if (!StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2364 size_t external_arrays = 0;
2365 for (MapAndHandler map_and_handler : target_maps_and_handlers) {
2366 DirectHandle<Map> map = map_and_handler.first;
2367 if (IsJSArrayMap(*map) && JSArray::MayHaveReadOnlyLength(*map)) {
2368 set_slow_stub_reason(
2369 "unsupported combination of arrays (potentially read-only length)");
2370 return;
2371
2372 } else if (map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2373 DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2374 external_arrays++;
2375 }
2376 }
2377 if (external_arrays != 0 &&
2378 external_arrays != target_maps_and_handlers.size()) {
2379 DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2380 set_slow_stub_reason(
2381 "unsupported combination of external and normal arrays");
2382 return;
2383 }
2384 }
2385
2386 StoreElementPolymorphicHandlers(&target_maps_and_handlers, store_mode);
2387 if (target_maps_and_handlers.empty()) {
2388 Handle<Object> handler = StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode);
2389 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
2390 } else if (target_maps_and_handlers.size() == 1) {
2391 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(),
2392 target_maps_and_handlers[0].first,
2393 target_maps_and_handlers[0].second);
2394 } else {
2395 ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), target_maps_and_handlers);
2396 }
2397}
2398
2399Handle<Object> KeyedStoreIC::StoreElementHandler(
2400 DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map, KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode,
2401 MaybeDirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> prev_validity_cell) {
2402 // The only case when could keep using non-slow element store handler for
2403 // a fast array with potentially read-only elements is when it's an
2404 // initializing store to array literal.
2405 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2406 !receiver_map->has_dictionary_elements() &&
2407 receiver_map->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2408 isolate()),
2409 IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2410
2411 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*receiver_map)) {
2412 // DefineKeyedOwnIC, which is used to define computed fields in instances,
2413 // should handled by the slow stub below instead of the proxy stub.
2414 if (IsJSProxyMap(*receiver_map) && !IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2415 return StoreHandler::StoreProxy(isolate());
2416 }
2417
2418 // Wasm objects or other kind of special objects go through the slow stub.
2419 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_SlowStub);
2420 return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2421 }
2422
2423 // TODO(ishell): move to StoreHandler::StoreElement().
2424 Handle<Code> code;
2425 if (receiver_map->has_sloppy_arguments_elements()) {
2426 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2427 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_KeyedStoreSloppyArgumentsStub);
2428 code = StoreHandler::StoreSloppyArgumentsBuiltin(isolate(), store_mode);
2429 } else if (receiver_map->has_fast_elements() ||
2430 receiver_map->has_sealed_elements() ||
2431 receiver_map->has_nonextensible_elements() ||
2432 receiver_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2433 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2434 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_StoreFastElementStub);
2435 if (IsJSArgumentsObjectMap(*receiver_map) &&
2436 receiver_map->has_fast_packed_elements()) {
2437 // Allow fast behaviour for in-bounds stores while making it miss and
2438 // properly handle the out of bounds store case.
2439 code = StoreHandler::StoreFastElementBuiltin(
2440 isolate(), KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds);
2441 } else {
2442 code = StoreHandler::StoreFastElementBuiltin(isolate(), store_mode);
2443 if (receiver_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2444 return code;
2445 }
2446 }
2447 } else if (IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC()) {
2448 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2449 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreInArrayLiteralIC_SlowStub);
2450 return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2451 } else {
2452 // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2453 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_StoreElementStub);
2454 DCHECK(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS == receiver_map->elements_kind() ||
2455 receiver_map->has_frozen_elements());
2456 return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2457 }
2458
2459 if (IsAnyDefineOwn() || IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC()) return code;
2460 DirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> validity_cell;
2461 if (!prev_validity_cell.ToHandle(&validity_cell)) {
2462 validity_cell =
2463 Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeChainValidityCell(receiver_map, isolate());
2464 }
2465 if (IsSmi(*validity_cell)) {
2466 // There's no prototype validity cell to check, so we can just use the stub.
2467 return code;
2468 }
2469 Handle<StoreHandler> handler = isolate()->factory()->NewStoreHandler(0);
2470 handler->set_validity_cell(*validity_cell);
2471 handler->set_smi_handler(*code);
2472 return handler;
2473}
2474
2475void KeyedStoreIC::StoreElementPolymorphicHandlers(
2476 MapsAndHandlers* receiver_maps_and_handlers,
2477 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode) {
2478 std::vector<Handle<Map>> receiver_maps;
2479 receiver_maps.reserve(receiver_maps_and_handlers->size());
2480 for (auto& [map, handler] : *receiver_maps_and_handlers) {
2481 receiver_maps.push_back(map);
2482 USE(handler);
2483 }
2484 for (size_t i = 0; i < receiver_maps_and_handlers->size(); i++) {
2485 Handle<Map> receiver_map = receiver_maps_and_handlers->at(i).first;
2486 DCHECK(!receiver_map->is_deprecated());
2487 MaybeObjectHandle old_handler = receiver_maps_and_handlers->at(i).second;
2488 Handle<Object> handler;
2489 DirectHandle<Map> transition;
2490
2491 if (receiver_map->instance_type() < FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE ||
2492 receiver_map->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2493 isolate())) {
2494 // TODO(mvstanton): Consider embedding store_mode in the state of the slow
2495 // keyed store ic for uniformity.
2496 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_SlowStub);
2497 handler = StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate());
2498
2499 } else {
2500 {
2501 Tagged<Map> tmap = receiver_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
2502 isolate(),
2503 MapHandlesSpan(receiver_maps.begin(), receiver_maps.end()),
2504 ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
2505 if (!tmap.is_null()) {
2506 if (receiver_map->is_stable()) {
2507 receiver_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
2508 }
2509 transition = direct_handle(tmap, isolate());
2510 }
2511 }
2512
2513 MaybeDirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> validity_cell;
2514 Tagged<HeapObject> old_handler_obj;
2515 if (!old_handler.is_null() &&
2516 (*old_handler).GetHeapObject(&old_handler_obj) &&
2517 IsDataHandler(old_handler_obj)) {
2518 validity_cell = direct_handle(
2519 Cast<DataHandler>(old_handler_obj)->validity_cell(), isolate());
2520 }
2521 // TODO(mythria): Do not recompute the handler if we know there is no
2522 // change in the handler.
2523 // TODO(mvstanton): The code below is doing pessimistic elements
2524 // transitions. I would like to stop doing that and rely on Allocation
2525 // Site Tracking to do a better job of ensuring the data types are what
2526 // they need to be. Not all the elements are in place yet, pessimistic
2527 // elements transitions are still important for performance.
2528 if (!transition.is_null()) {
2529 TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
2530 KeyedStoreIC_ElementsTransitionAndStoreStub);
2531 handler = StoreHandler::StoreElementTransition(
2532 isolate(), receiver_map, transition, store_mode, validity_cell);
2533 } else {
2534 handler = StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode, validity_cell);
2535 }
2536 }
2537 DCHECK(!handler.is_null());
2538 receiver_maps_and_handlers->at(i) =
2539 MapAndHandler(receiver_map, MaybeObjectHandle(handler));
2540 }
2541}
2542
2543namespace {
2544
2545bool MayHaveTypedArrayInPrototypeChain(Isolate* isolate,
2546 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
2547 for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *object); !iter.IsAtEnd();
2548 iter.Advance()) {
2549 // Be conservative, don't walk into proxies.
2550 if (IsJSProxy(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2551 if (IsJSTypedArray(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2552 }
2553 return false;
2554}
2555
2556KeyedAccessStoreMode GetStoreMode(DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
2557 size_t index) {
2558 bool oob_access = IsOutOfBoundsAccess(receiver, index);
2559 // Don't consider this a growing store if the store would send the receiver to
2560 // dictionary mode.
2561 bool allow_growth =
2562 IsJSArray(*receiver) && oob_access && index <= JSArray::kMaxArrayIndex &&
2563 !receiver->WouldConvertToSlowElements(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
2564 if (allow_growth) {
2565 return KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW;
2566 }
2567 if (receiver->map()->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements() &&
2568 oob_access) {
2569 return KeyedAccessStoreMode::kIgnoreTypedArrayOOB;
2570 }
2571 return receiver->elements()->IsCowArray() ? KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW
2572 : KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds;
2573}
2574
2575} // namespace
2576
2577MaybeHandle<Object> KeyedStoreIC::Store(Handle<JSAny> object,
2578 Handle<Object> key,
2579 Handle<Object> value) {
2580 // TODO(verwaest): Let SetProperty do the migration, since storing a property
2581 // might deprecate the current map again, if value does not fit.
2582 if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
2583 Handle<Object> result;
2584 // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefineKeyedOwnIC as a subclass of StoreIC
2585 // so the logic doesn't get mixed here.
2586 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2587 isolate(), result,
2588 IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()
2589 ? Runtime::DefineObjectOwnProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2590 StoreOrigin::kNamed)
2591 : Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2592 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed));
2593 return result;
2594 }
2595
2596 Handle<Object> store_handle;
2597
2598 intptr_t maybe_index;
2599 Handle<Name> maybe_name;
2600 KeyType key_type = TryConvertKey(key, isolate(), &maybe_index, &maybe_name);
2601
2602 if (key_type == kName) {
2603 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2604 isolate(), store_handle,
2605 StoreIC::Store(object, maybe_name, value, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed));
2606 if (vector_needs_update()) {
2607 if (ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key)) {
2608 set_slow_stub_reason("unhandled internalized string key");
2609 TraceIC("StoreIC", key);
2610 }
2611 }
2612 return store_handle;
2613 }
2614
2615 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtPrototype, isolate());
2616
2617 // TODO(jkummerow): Refactor the condition logic here and below.
2618 bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic &&
2619 !IsStringWrapper(*object) && !IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
2620 !IsJSGlobalProxy(*object);
2621 if (use_ic && !IsSmi(*object)) {
2622 // Don't use ICs for maps of the objects in Array's prototype chain. We
2623 // expect to be able to trap element sets to objects with those maps in
2624 // the runtime to enable optimization of element hole access.
2625 DirectHandle<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2626 if (heap_object->map()->IsMapInArrayPrototypeChain(isolate())) {
2627 set_slow_stub_reason("map in array prototype");
2628 use_ic = false;
2629 }
2630#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2631 if (IsWasmObjectMap(heap_object->map())) {
2632 set_slow_stub_reason("wasm object");
2633 use_ic = false;
2634 }
2635#endif
2636 }
2637
2638 Handle<Map> old_receiver_map;
2639 bool is_arguments = false;
2640 bool key_is_valid_index = (key_type == kIntPtr);
2641 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode = KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds;
2642 if (use_ic && IsJSReceiver(*object) && key_is_valid_index) {
2643 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
2644 old_receiver_map = handle(receiver->map(), isolate());
2645 is_arguments = IsJSArgumentsObject(*receiver);
2646 bool is_jsobject = IsJSObject(*receiver);
2647 size_t index;
2648 key_is_valid_index = IntPtrKeyToSize(maybe_index, receiver, &index);
2649 if (is_jsobject && !is_arguments && key_is_valid_index) {
2650 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver_object = Cast<JSObject>(object);
2651 store_mode = GetStoreMode(receiver_object, index);
2652 }
2653 }
2654
2655 DCHECK(store_handle.is_null());
2656 // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefineKeyedOwnIC as a subclass of StoreIC
2657 // so the logic doesn't get mixed here.
2658 MaybeHandle<Object> result =
2659 IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()
2660 ? Runtime::DefineObjectOwnProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2661 StoreOrigin::kNamed)
2662 : Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2663 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed);
2664 if (result.is_null()) {
2665 DCHECK(isolate()->has_exception());
2666 set_slow_stub_reason("failed to set property");
2667 use_ic = false;
2668 }
2669 if (use_ic) {
2670 if (!old_receiver_map.is_null()) {
2671 if (is_arguments) {
2672 set_slow_stub_reason("arguments receiver");
2673 } else if (IsJSArray(*object) && StoreModeCanGrow(store_mode) &&
2674 JSArray::HasReadOnlyLength(Cast<JSArray>(object))) {
2675 set_slow_stub_reason("array has read only length");
2676 } else if (IsJSObject(*object) &&
2677 MayHaveTypedArrayInPrototypeChain(isolate(),
2678 Cast<JSObject>(object))) {
2679 // Make sure we don't handle this in IC if there's any JSTypedArray in
2680 // the {receiver}'s prototype chain, since that prototype is going to
2681 // swallow all stores that are out-of-bounds for said prototype, and we
2682 // just let the runtime deal with the complexity of this.
2683 set_slow_stub_reason("typed array in the prototype chain");
2684 } else if (key_is_valid_index) {
2685 if (old_receiver_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) {
2686 set_slow_stub_reason("receiver with prototype map");
2687 } else if (old_receiver_map->has_dictionary_elements() ||
2688 !old_receiver_map
2689 ->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2690 isolate())) {
2691 // We should go generic if receiver isn't a dictionary, but our
2692 // prototype chain does have dictionary elements. This ensures that
2693 // other non-dictionary receivers in the polymorphic case benefit
2694 // from fast path keyed stores.
2695 DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2696 UpdateStoreElement(old_receiver_map, store_mode,
2697 handle(receiver->map(), isolate()));
2698 } else {
2699 set_slow_stub_reason("prototype with potentially read-only elements");
2700 }
2701 } else {
2702 set_slow_stub_reason("non-smi-like key");
2703 }
2704 } else {
2705 set_slow_stub_reason("non-JSObject receiver");
2706 }
2707 }
2708
2709 if (vector_needs_update()) {
2710 ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key);
2711 }
2712 TraceIC("StoreIC", key);
2713
2714 return result;
2715}
2716
2717namespace {
2718Maybe<bool> StoreOwnElement(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> array,
2719 Handle<Object> index, DirectHandle<Object> value) {
2720 DCHECK(IsNumber(*index));
2721 PropertyKey key(isolate, index);
2722 LookupIterator it(isolate, array, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
2723
2724 MAYBE_RETURN(JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
2725 &it, value, NONE, Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)),
2726 Nothing<bool>());
2727 return Just(true);
2728}
2729} // namespace
2730
2731MaybeHandle<Object> StoreInArrayLiteralIC::Store(DirectHandle<JSArray> array,
2732 Handle<Object> index,
2733 Handle<Object> value) {
2734 DCHECK(!array->map()->IsMapInArrayPrototypeChain(isolate()));
2735 DCHECK(IsNumber(*index));
2736
2737 if (!v8_flags.use_ic || state() == NO_FEEDBACK ||
2738 MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), array)) {
2739 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(StoreOwnElement(isolate(), array, index, value));
2740 TraceIC("StoreInArrayLiteralIC", index);
2741 return value;
2742 }
2743
2744 // TODO(neis): Convert HeapNumber to Smi if possible?
2745
2746 KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode = KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds;
2747 if (IsSmi(*index)) {
2748 DCHECK_GE(Smi::ToInt(*index), 0);
2749 uint32_t index32 = static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::ToInt(*index));
2750 store_mode = GetStoreMode(array, index32);
2751 }
2752
2753 Handle<Map> old_array_map(array->map(), isolate());
2754 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(StoreOwnElement(isolate(), array, index, value));
2755
2756 if (IsSmi(*index)) {
2757 DCHECK(!old_array_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map());
2758 UpdateStoreElement(old_array_map, store_mode,
2759 handle(array->map(), isolate()));
2760 } else {
2761 set_slow_stub_reason("index out of Smi range");
2762 }
2763
2764 if (vector_needs_update()) {
2765 ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, index);
2766 }
2767 TraceIC("StoreInArrayLiteralIC", index);
2768 return value;
2769}

2775RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadIC_Miss) {
2776 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2777 DCHECK_EQ(4, args.length());
2778 // Runtime functions don't follow the IC's calling convention.
2779 Handle<JSAny> receiver = args.at<JSAny>(0);
2780 Handle<Name> key = args.at<Name>(1);
2781 int slot = args.tagged_index_value_at(2);
2782 Handle<FeedbackVector> vector = args.at<FeedbackVector>(3);
2783 FeedbackSlot vector_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot);
2784
2785 // A monomorphic or polymorphic KeyedLoadIC with a string key can call the
2786 // LoadIC miss handler if the handler misses. Since the vector Nexus is
2787 // set up outside the IC, handle that here.
2788 FeedbackSlotKind kind = vector->GetKind(vector_slot);
2789 if (IsLoadICKind(kind)) {
2790 LoadIC ic(isolate, vector, vector_slot, kind);
2791 ic.UpdateState(receiver, key);
2792 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate, ic.Load(receiver, key));
2793
2794 } else if (IsLoadGlobalICKind(kind)) {
2795 DCHECK_EQ(isolate->native_context()->global_proxy(), *receiver);
2796 receiver = isolate->global_object();
2797 LoadGlobalIC ic(isolate, vector, vector_slot, kind);
2798 ic.UpdateState(receiver, key);
2799 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate, ic.Load(key));
2800
2801 } else {
2802 DCHECK(IsKeyedLoadICKind(kind));
2803 KeyedLoadIC ic(isolate, vector, vector_slot, kind);
2804 ic.UpdateState(receiver, key);
2805 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate, ic.Load(receiver, key));
2806 }
2807}

3261namespace {
3262
3263enum class FastCloneObjectMode {
3264 // The clone has the same map as the input.
3265 kIdenticalMap,
3266 // The clone is the empty object literal.
3267 kEmptyObject,
3268 // The clone has an empty object literal map.
3269 kDifferentMap,
3270 // The source map is to complicated to handle.
3271 kNotSupported,
3272 // Returned by PreCheck
3273 kMaybeSupported
3274};
3275
3276FastCloneObjectMode GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(DirectHandle<Map> map,
3277 bool null_proto_literal,
3278 Isolate* isolate) {
3279 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3280 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) {
3281 // Everything that produces the empty object literal can be supported since
3282 // we have a special case for that.
3283 if (null_proto_literal) return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3284 return IsNullOrUndefinedMap(*map) || IsBooleanMap(*map) ||
3285 IsHeapNumberMap(*map)
3286 ? FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject
3287 : FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3288 }
3289 ElementsKind elements_kind = map->elements_kind();
3290 if (!IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3291 !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3292 return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3293 }
3294 if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) {
3295 return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3296 }
3297
3298 // TODO(olivf): Think about cases where cross-context copies are safe.
3299 if (!map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context())) {
3300 return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3301 }
3302
3303 return FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported;
3304}
3305
3306FastCloneObjectMode GetCloneModeForMap(DirectHandle<Map> map,
3307 bool null_proto_literal,
3308 Isolate* isolate) {
3309 FastCloneObjectMode pre_check =
3310 GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(map, null_proto_literal, isolate);
3311 if (pre_check != FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported) {
3312 return pre_check;
3313 }
3314
3315 // The clone must always start from an object literal map, it must be an
3316 // instance of the object function, have the default prototype and not be a
3317 // prototype itself. Only if the source map fits that criterion we can
3318 // directly use it as the target map.
3319 FastCloneObjectMode mode =
3320 map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE &&
3321 !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(map->elements_kind()) &&
3322 map->GetConstructor() == *isolate->object_function() &&
3323 map->prototype() == *isolate->object_function_prototype() &&
3324 !map->is_prototype_map()
3325 ? FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap
3326 : FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3327
3328 if (null_proto_literal || IsNull(map->prototype())) {
3329 mode = FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3330 }
3331
3332 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
3333 for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3334 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3335 Tagged<Name> key = descriptors->GetKey(i);
3336 if (details.kind() != PropertyKind::kData || !details.IsEnumerable() ||
3337 key->IsPrivateName()) {
3338 return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3339 }
3340 if (!details.IsConfigurable() || details.IsReadOnly()) {
3341 mode = FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3342 }
3343 }
3344
3345 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap,
3346 !map->is_prototype_map());
3347
3348 return mode;
3349}
3350
3351bool CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(
3352 DirectHandle<Map> source_map, std::optional<DirectHandle<Map>> target_map,
3353 bool null_proto_literal, Isolate* isolate) {
3354 if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions || null_proto_literal) {
3355 return false;
3356 }
3357 // As of now any R/O source object should end up in the kEmptyObject case, but
3358 // there is not really a way of ensuring it. Thus, we also check it below.
3359 // This is a performance dcheck. If it fails, the clone IC does not handle a
3360 // case it probably could.
3361 // TODO(olivf): Either remove that dcheck or move it to GetCloneModeForMap.
3362 DCHECK(!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*source_map));
3363 if (HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*source_map) || source_map->is_deprecated() ||
3364 source_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3365 return false;
3366 }
3367 if (!target_map) {
3368 return true;
3369 }
3370 CHECK(!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(**target_map));
3371 return !(*target_map)->is_deprecated();
3372}
3373
3374// Check if an object with `source_map` can be cloned by `FastCloneJSObject`
3375// when the result shall have `target_map`. Optionally `override_map` is the map
3376// of an already existing object that will be written into. If no `override_map`
3377// is given, we assume that a fresh target object can be allocated with
3378// already the correct `target_map`.
3379bool CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3380 DirectHandle<Map> target_map,
3381 DirectHandle<Map> override_map,
3382 bool null_proto_literal,
3383 Isolate* isolate) {
3384 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3385 DCHECK(!target_map->is_deprecated());
3386 DCHECK(source_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3387 DCHECK(!source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3388 DCHECK(!target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3389 DCHECK_EQ(*target_map->map(), *source_map->map());
3390 DCHECK_EQ(target_map->GetConstructor(), *isolate->object_function());
3391 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
3392 !null_proto_literal,
3393 *target_map->prototype() == *isolate->object_function_prototype());
3394
3395 // Ensure source and target have identical binary represenation of properties
3396 // and elements as the IC relies on copying the raw bytes. This also excludes
3397 // cases with non-enumerable properties or accessors on the source object.
3398 if (source_map->instance_type() != JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
3399 target_map->instance_type() != JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
3400 !target_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties() ||
3401 !target_map->has_fast_elements()) {
3402 return false;
3403 }
3404 if (!override_map.is_null()) {
3405 // No cross-context object reuse.
3406 if (target_map->map() != override_map->map()) {
3407 return false;
3408 }
3409 // In case we want to clone into an existing target object, we must ensure
3410 // that this existing object has a compatible size. In particular we cannot
3411 // shrink or grow the already given object. We also exclude a different
3412 // start offset, since this doesn't allow us to change the object in-place
3413 // in a GC safe way.
3414 DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3415 DCHECK(override_map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE);
3416 DCHECK_EQ(override_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors(), 0);
3417 DCHECK(!override_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3418 if (override_map->instance_size() != target_map->instance_size() ||
3419 override_map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords() !=
3420 target_map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords()) {
3421 return false;
3422 }
3423 }
3424#ifdef DEBUG
3425 ElementsKind source_elements_kind = source_map->elements_kind();
3426 ElementsKind target_elements_kind = target_map->elements_kind();
3427 DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(source_elements_kind) ||
3428 IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(source_elements_kind));
3429 DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(target_elements_kind));
3430 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsHoleyElementsKindForRead(source_elements_kind),
3431 IsHoleyElementsKind(target_elements_kind));
3432#endif // DEBUG
3433 // There are no transitions between prototype maps.
3434 if (source_map->is_prototype_map() || target_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3435 return false;
3436 }
3437 // Exclude edge-cases like not copying a __proto__ property.
3438 if (source_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() !=
3439 target_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()) {
3440 return false;
3441 }
3442 // Check that the source inobject properties fit into the target.
3443 int source_used_inobj_properties = source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3444 source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3445 int target_used_inobj_properties = target_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3446 target_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3447 if (source_used_inobj_properties != target_used_inobj_properties) {
3448 return false;
3449 }
3450 // The properties backing store must be of the same size as the clone ic again
3451 // blindly copies it.
3452 if (source_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() !=
3453 target_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() ||
3454 (target_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() &&
3455 source_map->UnusedPropertyFields() !=
3456 target_map->UnusedPropertyFields())) {
3457 return false;
3458 }
3459 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = source_map->instance_descriptors();
3460 Tagged<DescriptorArray> target_descriptors =
3461 target_map->instance_descriptors();
3462 for (InternalIndex i : target_map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3463 if (descriptors->GetKey(i) != target_descriptors->GetKey(i)) {
3464 return false;
3465 }
3466 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3467 PropertyDetails target_details = target_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3468 DCHECK_EQ(details.kind(), PropertyKind::kData);
3469 DCHECK_EQ(target_details.kind(), PropertyKind::kData);
3470 Tagged<FieldType> type = descriptors->GetFieldType(i);
3471 Tagged<FieldType> target_type = target_descriptors->GetFieldType(i);
3472 // This DCHECK rests on the fact that we only clear field types when there
3473 // are no instances of the host map left. Thus, to enter the clone IC at
3474 // least one object of the source map needs to be created, which in turn
3475 // will re-initialize the source maps field type. This is guaranteed to also
3476 // update the target map through the sidestep transition, unless the target
3477 // map is deprecated.
3478 DCHECK(!IsNone(type));
3479 DCHECK(!IsNone(target_type));
3480 // With move_prototype_transitions_first enabled field updates don't
3481 // generalize across prototype transitions, because the transitions happen
3482 // on root maps (i.e., before any field is added). In other words we cannot
3483 // rely on changes in the source map propagating to the target map when
3484 // there is a SetPrototype involved. NB, technically without
3485 // move_prototype_transitions_first we also don't update field types across
3486 // prototype transitions, however we preemptively generalize all fields of
3487 // prototype transition target maps.
3488 bool prototype_transition_is_shortcutted =
3489 v8_flags.move_prototype_transitions_first &&
3490 source_map->prototype() != target_map->prototype();
3491 if (!prototype_transition_is_shortcutted &&
3492 CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, target_map,
3493 null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3494 if (!details.representation().fits_into(
3495 target_details.representation()) ||
3496 (target_details.representation().IsDouble() &&
3497 details.representation().IsSmi())) {
3498 return false;
3499 }
3500 if (!FieldType::NowIs(type, target_type)) {
3501 return false;
3502 }
3503 } else {
3504 // In the case we cannot connect the maps in the transition tree (e.g.,
3505 // the clone also involves a proto transition) we cannot keep track of
3506 // representation dependencies. We can only allow the most generic target
3507 // representation. The same goes for field types.
3508 if (!details.representation().MostGenericInPlaceChange().Equals(
3509 target_details.representation()) ||
3510 !IsAny(target_type)) {
3511 return false;
3512 }
3513 }
3514 }
3515 return true;
3516}

3518} // namespace
3519
3520static MaybeHandle<JSObject> CloneObjectSlowPath(Isolate* isolate,
3521 DirectHandle<Object> source,
3522 int flags) {
3523 Handle<JSObject> new_object;
3524 if (flags & ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype) {
3525 new_object = isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
3526 } else if (IsJSObject(*source) &&
3527 Cast<JSObject>(*source)->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) {
3528 Tagged<Map> source_map = Cast<JSObject>(*source)->map();
3529 // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) It might be interesting to pick a map with
3530 // more properties, depending how many properties are added by the
3531 // surrounding literal.
3532 int properties = source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3533 source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3534 DirectHandle<Map> map = isolate->factory()->ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(
3535 isolate->native_context(), properties);
3536 new_object = isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map);
3537 } else {
3538 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor(
3539 isolate->native_context()->object_function(), isolate);
3540 new_object = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(constructor);
3541 }
3542
3543 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*source)) {
3544 return new_object;
3545 }
3546
3547 MAYBE_RETURN(
3548 JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
3549 isolate, new_object, source,
3550 PropertiesEnumerationMode::kPropertyAdditionOrder, {}, false),
3551 MaybeHandle<JSObject>());
3552 return new_object;
3553}
3554
3555RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_CloneObjectIC_Slow) {
3556 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3557 DCHECK_EQ(2, args.length());
3558 DirectHandle<Object> source = args.at(0);
3559 int flags = args.smi_value_at(1);
3560 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate,
3561 CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3562}
3563
3564namespace {
3565
3566template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3567Tagged<Object> GetCloneTargetMap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3568 DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3569 static_assert(kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign ||
3570 kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject);
3571 if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) {
3572 return SideStepTransition::Empty;
3573 }
3574
3575 // Ensure we can follow the sidestep transition NativeContext-wise.
3576 if (!source_map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context())) {
3577 return SideStepTransition::Empty;
3578 }
3579 Tagged<Object> result = SideStepTransition::Empty;
3580 TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *source_map);
3581 if (transitions.HasSideStepTransitions()) {
3582 result = transitions.GetSideStepTransition(kind);
3583 if (result.IsHeapObject()) {
3584 // Exclude deprecated maps.
3585 auto map = Cast<Map>(result.GetHeapObject());
3586 bool is_valid = !map->is_deprecated();
3587 // In the case of object assign we need to check the prototype validity
3588 // cell on the override map. If the override map changed we cannot assume
3589 // that it is correct to set all properties without any getter/setter in
3590 // the prototype chain interfering.
3591 if constexpr (kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign) {
3592 if (is_valid) {
3593 DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3594 Tagged<Object> validity_cell = transitions.GetSideStepTransition(
3595 SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssignValidityCell);
3596 is_valid = validity_cell.IsHeapObject() &&
3597 Cast<Cell>(validity_cell)->value().ToSmi().value() ==
3598 Map::kPrototypeChainValid;
3599 }
3600 }
3601 if (V8_LIKELY(is_valid)) {
3602 if (result.IsHeapObject()) {
3603 CHECK_EQ(GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(source_map, false, isolate),
3604 FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported);
3605 }
3606 } else {
3607 result = SideStepTransition::Empty;
3608 }
3609 }
3610 }
3611#ifdef DEBUG
3612 FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3613 GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, false, isolate);
3614 if (result == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3615 switch (clone_mode) {
3616 case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported:
3617 case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3618 break;
3619 case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject:
3620 case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3621 DCHECK_EQ(kind, SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign);
3622 break;
3623 case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3624 UNREACHABLE();
3625 }
3626 } else if (result != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3627 Tagged<Map> target = Cast<Map>(result.GetHeapObject());
3628 switch (clone_mode) {
3629 case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3630 if (kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject) {
3631 DCHECK_EQ(*source_map, target);
3632 break;
3633 }
3634 DCHECK_EQ(kind, SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign);
3635 [[fallthrough]];
3636 case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3637 DCHECK(CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(source_map,
3638 direct_handle(target, isolate),
3639 override_map, false, isolate));
3640 break;
3641 default:
3642 UNREACHABLE();
3643 }
3644 } else {
3645 DCHECK_EQ(result, SideStepTransition::Empty);
3646 }
3647#endif // DEBUG
3648 return result;
3649}
3650
3651template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3652void SetCloneTargetMap(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> source_map,
3653 DirectHandle<Map> new_target_map,
3654 DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3655 if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) return;
3656 DCHECK(CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, new_target_map, false,
3657 isolate));
3658 DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3659 SideStepTransition::Empty);
3660 DCHECK(!new_target_map->is_deprecated());
3661
3662 // Adding this transition also ensures that when the source map field
3663 // generalizes, we also generalize the target map.
3664 DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(new_target_map->elements_kind()));
3665
3666 constexpr bool need_validity_cell =
3667 kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign;
3668 DirectHandle<Cell> validity_cell;
3669 if constexpr (need_validity_cell) {
3670 // Since we only clone into empty object literals we only need one validity
3671 // cell on that prototype chain.
3672 DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3673 validity_cell = Cast<Cell>(
3674 Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeChainValidityCell(override_map, isolate));
3675 }
3676 TransitionsAccessor::EnsureHasSideStepTransitions(isolate, source_map);
3677 TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *source_map);
3678 transitions.SetSideStepTransition(kind, *new_target_map);
3679 if constexpr (need_validity_cell) {
3680 transitions.SetSideStepTransition(
3681 SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssignValidityCell, *validity_cell);
3682 }
3683 DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3684 *new_target_map);
3685}
3686
3687template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3688void SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> source_map,
3689 DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3690 if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) return;
3691 DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3692 SideStepTransition::Empty);
3693 DCHECK(CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, {}, false, isolate));
3694 // Adding this transition also ensures that when the source map field
3695 // generalizes, we also generalize the target map.
3696 TransitionsAccessor::EnsureHasSideStepTransitions(isolate, source_map);
3697 TransitionsAccessor(isolate, *source_map)
3698 .SetSideStepTransition(kind, SideStepTransition::Unreachable);
3699 DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3700 SideStepTransition::Unreachable);
3701}
3702
3703} // namespace

3705RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_CloneObjectIC_Miss) {
3706 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3707 DCHECK_EQ(4, args.length());
3708 DirectHandle<Object> source = args.at(0);
3709 int flags = args.smi_value_at(1);
3710
3711 if (!MigrateDeprecated(isolate, source)) {
3712 Handle<HeapObject> maybe_vector = args.at<HeapObject>(3);
3713 std::optional<FeedbackNexus> nexus;
3714 if (IsFeedbackVector(*maybe_vector)) {
3715 int index = args.tagged_index_value_at(2);
3716 FeedbackSlot slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(index);
3717 nexus.emplace(isolate, Cast<FeedbackVector>(maybe_vector), slot);
3718 }
3719 if (!IsSmi(*source) && (!nexus || !nexus->IsMegamorphic())) {
3720 bool null_proto_literal = flags & ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype;
3721 Handle<Map> source_map(Cast<HeapObject>(source)->map(), isolate);
3722
3723 // In case we are still slack tracking let's defer a decision. The fast
3724 // case does not support it.
3725 if (!source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3726 auto UpdateNexus = [&](Handle<Object> target_map) {
3727 if (!nexus) return;
3728 nexus->ConfigureCloneObject(source_map,
3729 MaybeObjectHandle(target_map));
3730 };
3731 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3732 bool unsupported = false;
3733 if (!null_proto_literal) {
3734 auto maybe_target =
3735 GetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(
3736 isolate, source_map, {});
3737 if (maybe_target == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3738 unsupported = true;
3739 } else if (maybe_target != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3740 Handle<Map> target =
3741 handle(Cast<Map>(maybe_target.GetHeapObject()), isolate);
3742 UpdateNexus(target);
3743 return *target;
3744 }
3745 }
3746
3747 FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3748 unsupported
3749 ? FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported
3750 : GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, null_proto_literal, isolate);
3751 auto UpdateState = [&](Handle<Map> target_map) {
3752 UpdateNexus(target_map);
3753 if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, target_map,
3754 null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3755 SetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(
3756 isolate, source_map, target_map, {});
3757 }
3758 };
3759 switch (clone_mode) {
3760 case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap: {
3761 UpdateState(source_map);
3762 // When returning a map the IC miss handler re-starts from the top.
3763 return *source_map;
3764 }
3765 case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject: {
3766 UpdateNexus(handle(Smi::zero(), isolate));
3767 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(
3768 isolate, CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3769 }
3770 case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap: {
3771 DirectHandle<Object> res;
3772 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
3773 isolate, res, CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3774 Handle<Map> result_map(Cast<HeapObject>(res)->map(), isolate);
3775 if (result_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3776 return *res;
3777 }
3778 if (CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(
3779 source_map, result_map, {}, null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3780 DCHECK(result_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3781 DCHECK_EQ(source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3782 source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties(),
3783 result_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3784 result_map->UnusedInObjectProperties());
3785 UpdateState(result_map);
3786 } else {
3787 if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(
3788 source_map, {}, null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3789 SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported<
3790 SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(isolate, source_map,
3791 {});
3792 }
3793 if (nexus) {
3794 nexus->ConfigureMegamorphic();
3795 }
3796 }
3797 return *res;
3798 }
3799 case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported: {
3800 break;
3801 }
3802 case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3803 UNREACHABLE();
3804 }
3805 DCHECK(clone_mode == FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported);
3806 if (nexus) {
3807 nexus->ConfigureMegamorphic();
3808 }
3809 }
3810 }
3811 }
3812
3813 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate,
3814 CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3815}

3817RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_StoreCallbackProperty) {
3818 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = args.at<JSObject>(0);
3819 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = args.at<JSObject>(1);
3820 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info = args.at<AccessorInfo>(2);
3821 DirectHandle<Name> name = args.at<Name>(3);
3822 DirectHandle<Object> value = args.at(4);
3823 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3824
3825#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
3826 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TracingFlags::is_runtime_stats_enabled())) {
3827 RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(
3828 isolate, Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate, receiver, name, value,
3829 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed));
3830 }
3831#endif
3832
3833 PropertyCallbackArguments arguments(isolate, info->data(), *receiver, *holder,
3834 Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
3835 std::ignore = arguments.CallAccessorSetter(info, name, value);
3836 RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION(isolate);
3837 return *value;
3838}

3840namespace {
3841
3842bool MaybeCanCloneObjectForObjectAssign(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> source,
3843 DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3844 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
3845 Isolate* isolate) {
3846 FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3847 GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, false, isolate);
3848 switch (clone_mode) {
3849 case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3850 case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3851 break;
3852 case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported:
3853 return false;
3854 case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject:
3855 case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3856 // Cannot happen since we should only be called with JSObjects.
3857 UNREACHABLE();
3858 }
3859
3860 // We need to be sure that there are no setters or other nastiness installed
3861 // on the Object.prototype which clash with the properties we intende to copy.
3862 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
3863 auto res =
3864 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, source, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
3865 ONLY_ENUMERABLE, GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers);
3866 CHECK(res.ToHandle(&keys));
3867 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
3868 Handle<Object> next_key(keys->get(i), isolate);
3869 PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
3870 LookupIterator it(isolate, target, key);
3871 switch (it.state()) {
3872 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
3873 break;
3874 case LookupIterator::DATA:
3875 if (it.property_attributes() & PropertyAttributes::READ_ONLY) {
3876 return false;
3877 }
3878 break;
3879 default:
3880 return false;
3881 }
3882 }
3883 return true;
3884}
3885
3886} // namespace
3887
3888// Returns one of:
3889// * A map to be used with FastCloneJSObject
3890// * Undefined if fast cloning is not possible
3891// * True if assignment must be skipped (i.e., the runtime already did it)
3892RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_ObjectAssignTryFastcase) {
3893 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3894 DCHECK_EQ(2, args.length());
3895 auto source = Cast<JSReceiver>(args.at(0));
3896 auto target = Cast<JSReceiver>(args.at(1));
3897 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*source));
3898 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*target));
3899
3900 Handle<Map> source_map = handle(source->map(), isolate);
3901 Handle<Map> target_map = handle(target->map(), isolate);
3902
3903 DCHECK_EQ(target_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors(), 0);
3904 DCHECK(!source_map->is_dictionary_map());
3905 DCHECK(!target_map->is_dictionary_map());
3906 DCHECK(!source_map->is_deprecated());
3907 DCHECK(!target_map->is_deprecated());
3908 DCHECK(target_map->is_extensible());
3909 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*source, isolate) && !IsNull(*source, isolate));
3910 DCHECK(source_map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context()));
3911
3912 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3913 {
3914 Tagged<Object> maybe_clone_target =
3915 GetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3916 isolate, source_map, target_map);
3917 if (maybe_clone_target == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3918 return roots.undefined_value();
3919 } else if (maybe_clone_target != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3920 return Cast<Map>(maybe_clone_target.GetHeapObject());
3921 }
3922 }
3923
3924 auto UpdateCache = [&](Handle<Map> clone_target_map) {
3925 if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, clone_target_map, false,
3926 isolate)) {
3927 SetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3928 isolate, source_map, clone_target_map, target_map);
3929 }
3930 };
3931 auto UpdateCacheNotClonable = [&]() {
3932 if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, {}, false, isolate)) {
3933 SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3934 isolate, source_map, target_map);
3935 }
3936 };
3937
3938 // In case we are still slack tracking let's defer a decision. The fast case
3939 // does not support it.
3940 if (source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress() ||
3941 target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3942 return roots.undefined_value();
3943 }
3944
3945 if (MaybeCanCloneObjectForObjectAssign(source, source_map, target, isolate)) {
3946 CHECK(target->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3947 Maybe<bool> res = JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
3948 isolate, target, source, PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder);
3949 DCHECK(res.FromJust());
3950 USE(res);
3951 Handle<Map> clone_target_map = handle(target->map(), isolate);
3952 if (clone_target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3953 return roots.true_value();
3954 }
3955 if (CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(source_map, clone_target_map,
3956 target_map, false, isolate)) {
3957 CHECK(target->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3958 UpdateCache(clone_target_map);
3959 } else {
3960 UpdateCacheNotClonable();
3961 }
3962 // We already did the copying here. Thus, returning true to cause the
3963 // CSA builtin to skip assigning anything.
3964 return roots.true_value();
3965 }
3966 UpdateCacheNotClonable();
3967 return roots.undefined_value();
3968}
