3974RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadPropertyWithInterceptor) {
3975 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3976 DCHECK_EQ(5, args.length());
3977 DirectHandle<Name> name = args.at<Name>(0);
3978 DirectHandle<Object> receiver_arg = args.at(1);
3979 Handle<JSObject> holder = args.at<JSObject>(2);
3980
3981 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver;
3982 if (!TryCast<JSReceiver>(receiver_arg, &receiver)) {
3983 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
3984 isolate, receiver, Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver_arg));
3985 }
3986
3987 {
3988 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(holder->GetNamedInterceptor(),
3989 isolate);
3990 PropertyCallbackArguments arguments(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
3991 *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
3992
3993 DirectHandle<Object> result = arguments.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, name);
3994 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
3995 RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, arguments);
3996
3997 if (!result.is_null()) {
3998 arguments.AcceptSideEffects();
3999 return *result;
4000 }
4001 // If the interceptor didn't handle the request, then there must be no
4002 // side effects.
4003 }
4004
4005 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, name, holder);
4006 // Skip any lookup work until we hit the (possibly non-masking) interceptor.
4007 while (it.state() != LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR ||
4008 !it.GetHolder<JSObject>().is_identical_to(holder)) {
4009 DCHECK(it.state() != LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK || it.HasAccess());
4010 it.Next();
4011 }
4012 // Skip past the interceptor.
4013 it.Next();
4014 DirectHandle<Object> result;
4015 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result, Object::GetProperty(&it));
4016
4017 if (it.IsFound()) return *result;
4018
4019 int slot = args.tagged_index_value_at(3);
4020 DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> vector = args.at<FeedbackVector>(4);
4021 FeedbackSlot vector_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot);
4022 FeedbackSlotKind slot_kind = vector->GetKind(vector_slot);
4023 // It could actually be any kind of load IC slot here but the predicate
4024 // handles all the cases properly.
4025 if (!LoadIC::ShouldThrowReferenceError(slot_kind)) {
4026 return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
4027 }
4028
4029 // Throw a reference error.
4030 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_FAILURE(
4031 isolate, NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kNotDefined, it.name()));
4032}
4033
4034RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_StorePropertyWithInterceptor) {
4035 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4036 DCHECK_EQ(3, args.length());
4037 // Runtime functions don't follow the IC's calling convention.
4038 DirectHandle<Object> value = args.at(0);
4039 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = args.at<JSObject>(1);
4040 DirectHandle<Name> name = args.at<Name>(2);
4041
4042 // TODO(ishell): Cache interceptor_holder in the store handler like we do
4043 // for LoadHandler::kInterceptor case.
4044 DirectHandle<JSObject> interceptor_holder = receiver;
4045 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver) &&
4046 (!receiver->HasNamedInterceptor() ||
4047 receiver->GetNamedInterceptor()->non_masking())) {
4048 interceptor_holder =
4049 direct_handle(Cast<JSObject>(receiver->map()->prototype()), isolate);
4050 }
4051 DCHECK(interceptor_holder->HasNamedInterceptor());
4052 {
4053 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(
4054 interceptor_holder->GetNamedInterceptor(), isolate);
4055
4056 DCHECK(!interceptor->non_masking());
4057 // TODO(ishell, 348688196): why is it known that it shouldn't throw?
4058 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw = Just(kDontThrow);
4059 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4060 *receiver, should_throw);
4061
4062 v8::Intercepted intercepted =
4063 args.CallNamedSetter(interceptor, name, value);
4064 // Stores initiated by StoreICs don't care about the exact result of
4065 // the store operation returned by the callback as long as it doesn't
4066 // throw an exception.
4067 constexpr bool ignore_return_value = true;
4068 InterceptorResult result;
4069 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
4070 isolate, result,
4071 args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Setter", ignore_return_value));
4072
4073 switch (result) {
4074 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
4075 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
4076 return *value;
4077
4078 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
4079 // Proceed storing past the interceptor.
4080 break;
4081 }
4082 }
4083
4084 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, name, receiver);
4085 // Skip past any access check on the receiver.
4086 while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4087 DCHECK(it.HasAccess());
4088 it.Next();
4089 }
4090 // Skip past the interceptor on the receiver.
4091 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it.state());
4092 it.Next();
4093
4094 MAYBE_RETURN(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kNamed),
4095 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception());
4096 return *value;
4097}

4099RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadElementWithInterceptor) {
4100 // TODO(verwaest): This should probably get the holder and receiver as input.
4101 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4102 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = args.at<JSObject>(0);
4103 DCHECK_GE(args.smi_value_at(1), 0);
4104 uint32_t index = args.smi_value_at(1);
4105
4106 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(receiver->GetIndexedInterceptor(),
4107 isolate);
4108 PropertyCallbackArguments arguments(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4109 *receiver, Just(kDontThrow));
4110 DirectHandle<Object> result = arguments.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, index);
4111 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
4112 RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, arguments);
4113
4114 if (result.is_null()) {
4115 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, index, receiver);
4116 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it.state());
4117 it.Next();
4118 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
4119 Object::GetProperty(&it));
4120 }
4121
4122 return *result;
4123}

4145RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_HasElementWithInterceptor) {
4146 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4147 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = args.at<JSObject>(0);
4148 DCHECK_GE(args.smi_value_at(1), 0);
4149 uint32_t index = args.smi_value_at(1);
4150
4151 {
4152 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(receiver->GetIndexedInterceptor(),
4153 isolate);
4154 PropertyCallbackArguments arguments(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4155 *receiver, Just(kDontThrow));
4156
4157 if (!IsUndefined(interceptor->query(), isolate)) {
4158 DirectHandle<Object> result =
4159 arguments.CallIndexedQuery(interceptor, index);
4160 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
4161 RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, arguments);
4162 if (!result.is_null()) {
4163 int32_t value;
4164 CHECK(Object::ToInt32(*result, &value));
4165 // TODO(ishell): PropertyAttributes::ABSENT is not exposed in the Api,
4166 // so it can't be officially returned. We should fix the tests instead.
4167 if (value == ABSENT) return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).false_value();
4168 arguments.AcceptSideEffects();
4169 return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).true_value();
4170 }
4171 } else if (!IsUndefined(interceptor->getter(), isolate)) {
4172 DirectHandle<Object> result =
4173 arguments.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, index);
4174 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
4175 RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, arguments);
4176 if (!result.is_null()) {
4177 arguments.AcceptSideEffects();
4178 return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).true_value();
4179 }
4180 }
4181 // If the interceptor didn't handle the request, then there must be no
4182 // side effects.
4183 }
4184
4185 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, index, receiver);
4186 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it.state());
4187 it.Next();
4188 Maybe<bool> maybe = JSReceiver::HasProperty(&it);
4189 if (maybe.IsNothing()) return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception();
4190 return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).boolean_value(maybe.FromJust());
4191}
4192
4193} // namespace internal
4194} // namespace v8
